Video Title: 66. Databricks | Pyspark | Delta: Z-Order Command
Video Description:
Azure Databricks Learning: Delta Lake - Z-Order Command
========================================================

What is Z-order Command in delta table and how to apply in delta lake development?
Z-order one of the performance optimization techinique used in delta lake. It is used along with optimize command and used to compact small files into optimal size and at the same time relevant data is co-located to improve the performance.

This video gives complete understanding of Z-order command

Video Description:
🔥🔥Difference between Data Analyst and Data Scientist.🔥🔥
---------------------------------
Data Analysts 🔥
----------------------------------
✅Data detectives.
✅Gather, process, and analyze large datasets.
✅Perform statistical analyses.
✅Goal: Uncover trends, correlations, and insights for business decisions.
--------------------------
Data Scientists 🔥
---------------------------
✅Wizards of data.
✅Analyze data.
✅Develop algorithms and predictive models.
✅Goal: Forecast future trends by working with complex datasets.

--------------------------
Key Differences🔥
----------------------------
Data Analysts🔥
---------------------------
✅Analyze existing data.
✅Provide reports.

Data Scientists🔥
----------------------------
✅Forecast future trends.
✅Build predictive models.
✅Work with more complex datasets.

Welcome to Episode 09 of the Statistics for Data Science series, hosted by Vaibhav! In today’s session, we dive deep into Correlation, one of the foundational concepts in data science and data analytics. Understanding how variables relate to each other is essential for building predictive models and deriving actionable insights from your data.

This live session will cover the basics of correlation, including how to measure the strength and direction of relationships between two variables. Video Title: What are the Top 5 Roles in Data Science | Career Opportunities in Data Science Explained | #shorts
Video Description:
Can Data scientist work as a Data Analyst?
What’s the difference between Applied and Research Scientist?
Is ML engineer and Data Scientist the same?

There are so many job roles in the Data Science and Machine Learning industry which can overwhelm you in understanding the differences between them.

In this video, Srikanth Varma, co-founder of Applied Roots, breaks down the 5 most common job roles in the industry, and explains the key differences between each role, so you can be clear about what you're looking for in your next career move.

What is Data Science? 
Data science is a field that uses scientific methods, processes, algorithms and systems to extract knowledge and insights from structured and unstructured Data, and apply insights from data across a broad range of application domains. Data science combines the scientific method, math and statistics, specialised programming, and advanced analytics, to uncover and explain the insights buried in data.  

What is Machine Learning?
Machine learning (ML) is the study of computer algorithms that can improve automatically through experience and by the use of data .It is seen as a part of artificial intelligence. Machine learning algorithms build a model based on sample data, known as training data, in order to make predictions or decisions without being explicitly programmed to do so. 

Busting Data Science Myths: 
It’s easier now than ever before for ideas to spread around the world, including through fact-based communities like the one inhabited by data scientists. However, that doesn’t necessarily mean that every data science “fact” we hear is actually truthful.

In fact, some commonly known “facts” are little more than hearsay, misinterpretations, or, at worst, outright myths.

Python Programming Language: 
Python is the most widely used data science programming language in the world today. It is an open-source, easy-to-use language that has been around since the year 1991. This general-purpose and dynamic language is inherently object-oriented. It also supports multiple paradigms, from functional to structured and procedural programming. Therefore, it is one of the most popular languages for data science as well. With less than 1000 iterations, it is faster and a better option for data manipulations. 

What is A/B testing?
A/B testing, also known as split testing, refers to a randomised experimentation process wherein two or more versions of a variable (web page, page element, etc.) are shown to different segments of website visitors at the same time to determine which version leaves the maximum impact and drive business metrics. Essentially, A/B testing eliminates all the guesswork out of website optimisation and enables experience optimisers to make data-backed decisions.

Video Title: 🔥Salary of Data Scientist in US | Simplilearn | #Shorts #Datascience
Video Description:
Curious about a career in data science? In this short, we dive into a quick Q&A with a data scientist to find out what they do, how to get started, and what kind of salary you can expect in the field!

Our data scientist explains their role as working with large datasets, building predictive models, and discovering valuable insights to solve real-world problems. It’s all about math, stats, and mastering programming languages like Python and R. Plus, tools like TensorFlow and scikit-learn are essential for machine learning and AI projects.

Interested in breaking into the field? Start by getting strong fundamentals in math and stats, learn programming, and work on your own projects to build your portfolio. Hackathons and conferences are great ways to stay updated and connect with others in the field.

And what about the salary? In the US, entry-level data scientists typically make between $85,000 to $130,000 a year, with potential for even more in major cities like San Francisco or New York, where salaries can exceed $129,173.

Watch the full video to learn more about this exciting and lucrative field!

#DataScience #DataScientist #MachineLearning #Python #TensorFlow #CareerInTech #TechJobs #Salary #AI #BigData #Hackathons #LearnDataScience

Video Title: 🔥Data Analyst Vs Data Scientist | Which is better for you ? #Shorts #Simplilearn
Video Description:
In this video on Data Analyst Vs Data Scientist, we dive deep into the world of data to explore the key differences between Data Analysts and Data Scientists. If you're considering a career in data or just curious about the roles, this video is perfect for you! We'll break down the primary responsibilities, skill sets, and tools used by Data Analysts and Data Scientists, helping you understand what sets these two crucial positions apart.

A Data Analyst typically focuses on interpreting existing data to generate actionable insights for business decision-making. They are skilled in data visualization, SQL, and statistical analysis, working closely with various departments to optimize processes and strategies.

On the other hand, a Data Scientist goes a step further by building models to predict future trends and uncover deeper insights. They leverage advanced programming skills, machine learning algorithms, and big data technologies to solve complex problems and drive innovation.

By the end of this video, you'll have a clear understanding of which career path might be the best fit for you based on your interests and skillset. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe for more insightful content on data careers and trends. If you have any questions, drop them in the comments below!

Data Analysts interpret existing data, while Data Scientists predict future trends with advanced models.

Data Analysts need skills in data visualization, SQL, and statistical analysis.

✅What tools do Data Scientists use?

Data Scientists use Python, R, machine learning frameworks, and big data technologies.

Video Title: Introduction to Data Science with Python
Video Description:
Every single minute, computers across the world collect millions of gigabytes of data. What can you do to make sense of this mountain of data? How do data scientists use this data for the applications that power our modern world?

Data science is an ever-evolving field, using algorithms and scientific methods to parse complex data sets. Data scientists use a range of programming languages, such as Python and R, to harness and analyze data. This course focuses on using Python in data science. By the end of the course, you’ll have a fundamental understanding of machine learning models and basic concepts around Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). 

Using Python, learners will study regression models (Linear, Multilinear, and Polynomial) and classification models (kNN, Logistic), utilizing popular libraries such as sklearn, Pandas, matplotlib, and numPy. The course will cover key concepts of machine learning such as: picking the right complexity, preventing overfitting, regularization, assessing uncertainty, weighing trade-offs, and model evaluation. Participation in this course will build your confidence in using Python, preparing you for more advanced study in Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI), and advancement in your career.
 
Learners must have a minimum baseline of programming knowledge (preferably in Python) and statistics in order to be successful in this course. Python prerequisites can be met with an introductory Python course offered through CS50’s Introduction to Programming with Python, and statistics prerequisites can be met via Fat Chance or with Stat110 offered through HarvardX.

Learn more: https://www.harvardonline.harvard.edu

✅ What factors influence the salary of a Data Scientist?
The salary of a Data Scientist is influenced by several factors, including experience level, location, industry, and the specific skills they bring to the table. Advanced knowledge in areas like machine learning, big data, and specialized tools can lead to higher compensation. Additionally, companies in tech hubs or sectors like finance and healthcare often offer higher salaries due to the critical nature of data-driven decision-making in these industries.

✅ How does the demand for Data Scientists impact their salaries?
The high demand for Data Scientists has a significant impact on their salaries. As more companies rely on data to drive business decisions, the need for skilled professionals who can analyze and interpret complex datasets has surged. This demand, combined with a relatively limited supply of qualified Data Scientists, drives salaries upward, making data science one of the most lucrative careers in the tech industry.

Video Title: 🔥Data Scientist Vs Data Analyst | Who is Best: Data Analyst or Scientist? | Intellipaat #Shorts
Video Description:
In this video on 'Which is Better: Data Analyst or Data Scientist?' we delve into a playful debate between two seasoned professionals to determine which job role comes out on top. This video offers a humorous interpretation of the differences between a data scientist and a data analyst.

Generally, Data Analysts focus on interpreting existing data to generate actionable insights for business decisions. They excel in data visualization, SQL, and statistical analysis, working closely with various departments to optimize processes.

On the other hand, Data Scientists take a more advanced approach by building models to predict future trends and uncover deeper insights. They utilize advanced programming skills, machine learning algorithms, and big data technologies to solve complex problems and drive innovation.

By the end of the video, you'll have asked your opinion about who's better Data Analyst vs Scientist, so don't forget to drop your thoughts in the comment section below.

#DataAnalystVsDataScientist #DataScienceVsDataAnalytics #DataAnalyticsVsDataScience #DataAnalyst #DataScientist #DataScientistVsDataAnalyst #DataAnalystSalary #DataScientistSalary #Data #Shorts #TechShorts #ShortsVideo #ShortsFeed #ShortsViral #Intellipaat 

✅ Which is better data analyst or data scientist?
Whether a Data Analyst or Data Scientist is better depends on your career goals. If you prefer working with existing data to generate actionable insights, Data Analysis might be a better fit. However, if you enjoy building predictive models and solving complex problems with advanced programming, Data Science could be the ideal path.

✅ Is a data scientist harder than a data analyst?
Yes, being a Data Scientist is generally considered more challenging than being a Data Analyst. Data Scientists require advanced skills in programming, machine learning, and big data technologies, while Data Analysts focus more on data visualization, SQL, and statistical analysis. The complexity of tasks in Data Science often involves deeper technical knowledge and problem-solving abilities.

Video Title: What Does a Data Scientist Actually Do?
Video Description:
👉Sign up for Our Complete Data Science Training with 57% OFF: https://bit.ly/3sJATc9
👉 Download Our Free Data Science Career Guide: https://bit.ly/47Eh6d5

Many videos provide tips on becoming a data scientist—learning the necessary skills and the expected salaries in the field. But there isn’t nearly as much content that describes what data scientists do on the job. Today, we’ll address this topic.  
Contrary to what many business stakeholders believe, a data scientist isn’t a magician who can use AI to fix any problem.  
A data scientist’s primary purpose isn’t to pull data from the database either . 
A company that thrives—thanks to its data scientists—can educate those  within the organization that a data scientist’s primary goal is to create business value by using data . A data scientist’s role encompasses different activities, many of which we will describe in this video. Still, the first and most crucial point we need to remember is that the end goal of each task of a data scientist is to create business value. 
Therefore—besides solid statistics knowledge and an ability to use such coding languages as Python, R, and SQL—data scientists need business and communication skills to be successful in their work .

Video Title: Data Science And Data Analytics - Key Differences | Data Science vs Data Analytics | Intellipaat
Video Description:
#DataScienceAndDataAnalytics #DataScienceVsDataAnalytics #ShortsVideo #ShortsFeed #Intellipaat 

In this video on “Data Science vs Data Analytics," we will look into the key differences between Data Science and Data Analytics.  Data Science is the process that includes acquiring data, cleaning data, exploring data, and building models. Data Analytics is the process of using these models to draw conclusions and make predictions.

✅ Which is better, data science or data analytics?
Choosing between a career in data science and data analysis ultimately depends on your interests and strengths. If you are inclined towards more technical, algorithmic challenges and enjoy delving deep into machine learning and predictive modeling, data science might be the right path.

✅Does data science pay more than data analytics?
Both data analytics and data science have lots of room for growth when it comes to salary and responsibilities. The average annual salary for a Data Analyst is $64,000 and the average annual salary for a Data Scientist is $127,000. As you can see, the average salary for a Data Scientist is higher.

✅Does a data analyst require coding?
Data analysts need to be able to work with large datasets, use statistical methods to analyze the data, and apply mathematical models to interpret the results. They may also need programming languages like Python and R to write and run statistical models and algorithms.

Video Title: What Do Data Scientists ACTUALLY Do? | Life as a Data Scientist | Intellipaat #Shorts #DataScientist
Video Description:
Ever wondered what Data Scientists ACTUALLY do? 🤔 In this #shorts, we give you a quick insight into the daily life of a Data Scientist, from analyzing complex data to building models that drive business decisions. Discover the key responsibilities, tools, and tasks that define a career in data science, and what makes it one of the most sought-after jobs in tech today! 💻📊

Key Topics:
What Do Data Scientists Do
Data Scientist Job Role
Day in the Life of a Data Scientist

Watch now to learn what it takes to thrive in data science! 🚀

✅ What do data scientists do?
Data scientists analyze and interpret complex data to help organizations make informed decisions. They use statistical techniques, machine learning, and programming tools like Python or R to clean, process, and model data. Their work involves identifying patterns, building predictive models, and presenting insights to stakeholders. Ultimately, they turn raw data into actionable business strategies.

✅ What does the Life of a data scientist look like?
The life of a data scientist involves working with large datasets, cleaning and analyzing them to uncover insights. Their day typically includes coding, building machine learning models, and collaborating with teams to solve business problems. They spend time experimenting with algorithms and presenting findings to stakeholders. It’s a mix of technical work, problem-solving, and communication, offering both challenges and creativity.

Video Title: Data Scientist Kaise Bane? | How to Become a Data Scientist in 2025 | Intellipaat #Shorts
Video Description:
Want to know data scientist kaise bane in 2025? Data science is one of the most in-demand careers today, but many people still wonder, "Is data science worth it in 2025?" or "Should I still learn data science?" In this video, we break down everything about how to become a data scientist, including the skills, tools, career path, and opportunities in this exciting field.

If you’ve been searching for answers to data scientist kaise ban sakte hain or data scientist ka kaam kya hota hai, this video will give you a clear roadmap. Whether you're a fresher or an experienced professional looking to transition, data science offers immense potential for growth.

Why Learn Data Science?
✔️ High demand for data scientists in 2025 and beyond
✔️ Lucrative salaries and career growth opportunities
✔️ Applications in industries like finance, healthcare, e-commerce, and AI
✔️ Hands-on learning with real-world projects

FAQs:
❓ Is data science a good career in 2025?
Yes! Data science continues to be in high demand. If you learn the right skills and work on projects, you can secure a high-paying job in this field. If you are thinking, "Is data scientist a good career?", the answer is a resounding yes!

❓ Is data science good for freshers?
Absolutely! Many freshers enter the industry by learning data science fundamentals, working on projects, and gaining hands-on experience. Data scientist ka kaam kya hota hai? They analyze data, build models, and help businesses make informed decisions.

As a data scientist at NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory, Asitang is paving the path to some of the space world's most complex challenges with wit, innovation, charm, and true intellect. Video Title: Data Scientist Salary In India | How Much Does A Data Scientist Make ? | Simplilearn
Video Description:
In this video on Data Scientist Salary In India, explore the dynamic landscape of Data Scientist salaries in India. Gain valuable insights into the factors influencing compensation, industry trends, and regional variations. Discover the skills and qualifications that can elevate your earning potential in this high-demand field. Whether you're a seasoned professional or aspiring to enter the world of data science, understanding the salary dynamics in India is crucial. Join us to unravel the intricacies of Data Scientist salaries and empower yourself to make informed career decisions.

Data science has emerged as one of the most sought-after professions globally, and India is no exception. But what exactly is the earning potential of a data scientist in the Indian job market? In this comprehensive exploration, we delve deep into the intricacies of data scientist salaries in India, shedding light on the factors influencing these figures and unraveling the journey to becoming a data scientist.

Experience plays a pivotal role in determining a data scientist's salary. Entry-level professionals typically start with lower salaries compared to mid-level and senior data scientists. As they gain expertise and climb the corporate ladder, their earning potential increases significantly. However, it's essential to note that these figures are not set in stone and can vary based on various factors such as industry, location, and employer.

So, how does one embark on the journey to becoming a data scientist in India? The path to this lucrative career typically begins with acquiring a solid educational foundation. While a bachelor's degree in computer science, mathematics, statistics, or a related field is often the starting point, many aspiring data scientists opt to pursue advanced degrees such as master's or Ph.D. programs in data science, machine learning, or artificial intelligence to deepen their knowledge and enhance their credentials.

However, formal education alone is not enough. Data science is a multidisciplinary field that requires a diverse skill set encompassing programming, statistics, machine learning, data visualization, and domain expertise. Aspiring data scientists often engage in self-study, online courses, boot camps, and hands-on projects to hone their skills and stay abreast of the latest industry trends and technologies.

Furthermore, gaining practical experience through internships, freelance projects, or industry collaborations is crucial for transitioning into a full-fledged data scientist role. Many companies also value certifications from reputable organizations such as IBM, Microsoft, Google, or Cloudera, which validate an individual's proficiency in specific data science tools and techniques.

In conclusion, the journey to becoming a data scientist in India is both challenging and rewarding. With the right blend of education, skills, experience, and determination, individuals can carve out successful careers in this dynamic field while enjoying competitive salaries and ample opportunities for growth and innovation.

With AI and automation evolving rapidly, many professionals and freshers are asking: Should I still learn data science? 🤖 and Is data science a good career choice for the future? You’ll learn about the skills required, the projects you can work on, and the salary you can expect. The video also includes tips on how to get started in the field.
 
✅ Is data science a good career in 2024?
Opting for a career in data science promises not only job security but also financial rewards. As we step into 2024, this demand is expected to surge even higher. More industries have come to realize that data science holds the key to their future success.

✅ Is data science still in demand in 2025?
In the ever-evolving landscape of technology and information, the field of data science stands out as a beacon of opportunity. While predicting the future with absolute certainty is impossible, current trends and forecasts point towards a substantial surge in data science jobs in 2025 and beyond.

✅ Will AI replace data analysts?
Generative AI has the potential to automate certain aspects of data analysis, but it is unlikely to replace human creativity and strategic thinking. Instead of eliminating the role of data analysts, AI will enhance their capabilities and allow them to focus on higher-value tasks.

Video Title: Data Science Interview Questions | Top 40 Data Science Interview Questions & Answers | Intellipaat
Video Description:
This Data Science Interview Questions video will teach you the most frequently asked questions in any data science interview. If you want to advance your career in data science, this video will introduce you with the top theoretical, practical, and conceptual questions that you can expect in a data science interview.

Here are some top data science interview questions and answers that you may encounter in a data science job interview. These include questions about data science, supervised and unsupervised learning, the bias-variance tradeoff, cross-validation, and the curse of dimensionality.

🔵 Why Learn Data Science?
There are several reasons why learning data science can be beneficial:

✅ Data science is a highly in-demand field, with a shortage of qualified professionals. This means that data scientists often have good job prospects and can command high salaries.
✅ Data science is a multidisciplinary field, combining aspects of computer science, statistics, and domain expertise. This makes it a challenging and rewarding field to work in.
✅ Data science has the potential to solve real-world problems and make a positive impact on society. For example, data science can be used to improve healthcare, transportation, and education.
✅ Data science skills are transferable, meaning that they can be applied to a wide range of industries and job roles.
✅ Learning data science can help you develop valuable skills such as problem-solving, critical thinking, and communication.

Overall, learning data science can be a rewarding and fulfilling career choice with many benefits.

Video Title: Data Analyst vs Data Scientist: Pahami 3 Perbedaannya!💯
Video Description:
Dalam dunia data, peran Data Analyst dan Data Scientist memiliki perbedaan yang signifikan. Data Analyst menganalisis data, menemukan pola, dan memberikan wawasan yang didasarkan pada data yang ada. Mereka berfokus pada pengolahan data, menggunakan alat analisis, dan visualisasi informasi.
Di sisi lain, Data Scientist memiliki pendekatan yang lebih mendalam dan kompleks. Mereka menggabungkan statistik, pemrograman, dan machine learning untuk mengembangkan model prediktif yang canggih. Mereka juga bertugas mengumpulkan, membersihkan, dan memproses data secara mendalam.

#HowtoGetJobAsAFresherDataScientist #DataScienceRoadmap #PodcastClip #Intellipaat

Get ready to explore the world of Data Science with our Intellipaat Podcast episode focusing on Data Science Roadmap 2024.

In this video, our esteemed guest, Mr.Parth Sharma, the Senior Manager of Data Science @ Piramal Finance will tell us “How to Get A Job As A Fresher Data Scientist ” 
Stay tuned!

✅How to get a job in data science with no experience?
Build a Solid Data Science Foundation. 
Get Relevant Hands-on Experience. 
Build a Data Science Portfolio. 
Network and Find a Mentor. 
Create an Impressive Resume. 
Reach Out to Companies for Entry-Level Jobs.

✅How much does a fresher data scientist earn?
Data Scientist salary in Bengaluru/Bangalore with less than 1 year of experience to 8 years ranges from ₹ 4.0 Lakhs to ₹ 26.0 Lakhs with an average annual salary of ₹ 14.9 Lakhs based on 11.6k latest salaries.

✅How do I start working as a data scientist?
Earn a data science degree. Employers generally like to see some academic credentials to ensure you have the know-how to tackle a data science job, though it's not always required. 
Sharpen relevant skills. 
Get an entry-level data analytics job. 
Prepare for data science interviews.

Video Title: What is Data Science Project Life Cycle Explained Step by Step | ML Lifecycle Steps

In today's data-driven world, data science has become an indispensable part of businesses and organizations. However, embarking on a data science project can be a daunting task, and it's crucial to understand the various stages involved in the data science project lifecycle.

In this video, we'll be taking a deep dive on steps in data science project lifecycle, starting with the initial planning and data acquisition stages, where we define the problem statement and gather the necessary data. We'll then move on to the data cleaning and exploratory analysis stage, where we analyze the data and transform it into a suitable format for modeling.

Next, we'll discuss the modeling stage, where we develop a model to solve the problem at hand. We'll also cover the model evaluation and refinement stage, where we assess the performance of our model and make improvements as necessary. Finally, we'll conclude with the deployment and communication stage, where we present our findings and deploy the model for use in production.

Throughout this video, we'll be providing insights and best practices for each stage of the project lifecycle, as well as examples and case studies to illustrate how these stages apply in real-world scenarios.

Whether you're a data science practitioner or a business leader looking to understand the data science or step by step machine learning project lifecycle, this video is the perfect resource for you. So sit back, relax, and join us on this exciting journey through the data science project lifecycle.

Video Title: How Much Maths is Enough Maths for Data Science? #maths  #statistics  #datascience  #calculus
Video Description:
How much maths is enough maths for data science? Well, you don’t need to know everything! Here’s the math that matters!

First, Statistics!
Understand concepts like probability, hypothesis testing, and regression analysis for data analysis and inferences.

Second, Linear Algebra!
 Familiarity with matrices, vectors, and linear transformations is crucial, especially in machine learning.

 Third, Calculus!
Basic knowledge of differentiation and integration helps with optimization algorithms and understanding machine learning principles.

What Is Big Data?
Big data refers to the vast volume, variety, and velocity of data that exceeds traditional processing methods. It encompasses structured, unstructured, and semi-structured data from various sources, offering valuable insights for informed decision-making. Big data requires advanced analytics and scalable infrastructure to extract patterns, optimize operations, and gain comprehensive understanding for transformative impact.

Video Title: Wie wird man Data Scientist?
Video Description:
💠 Mein komplettes Produktivitätssystem: https://fokus.so



Data Science, was ist das überhaupt? Was macht ein Data Scientist? Was muss man lernen, wenn man eine Data Science Karriere anstrebt? Diese Fragen beantworte ich im heutigen Video.

Dem Beruf des Data Scientists wurde schon 2009 von Hal Varian und einige Jahre später dem Harvard Business Review eine glorreiche Zukunft vorhergesagt. Diese Vorhersage ist eingetreten, Daten spielen eine wichtigere Rolle denn je, und Data Scientists sind auf dem Arbeitsmarkt extrem gefragt.

Data Science ist allerdings ein recht allgemeiner Begriff ("Wissenschaft mit Daten"), der sich in viele Unterbereiche aufgliedern lässt, zum Beispiel: Messung & Metriken, Strategie, Vorhersagen (Time Series Analysis), Korrelationen, Experimente (AB-Tests), Data Engineering (Logging, ETL-Pipelines), Modellierung, Optimierung, Visualisierung, Maschinelles Lernen, Künstliche Intelligenz.

Hinzu kommt, dass man sich mit jedem dieser Bereiche auf einer von drei Stufen beschäftigen kann:
1) Grundlagenforschung (Level: Professor)
2) Angewandte Forschung bzw. Core Data Science (Level: PhD)
3) Anwendung bzw. Product Data Science (Level: Bachelor/Master/PhD)

Um als typischer Data Scientist in einer Firma zu arbeiten, sollte man mathematische Vorkenntnisse haben. Bewerber kommen üblicherweise aus Feldern wie: Informatik, Physik, Mathematik, Wirtschaftswissenschaften, Maschinenbau, Psychologie, ...

Vor allem die Statistik spielt in fast allen Bereichen eine immense Rolle. Darüber hinaus ist ein guter Data Scientist mit Python und/oder R bewandert und hat gute Kommunikationsfähigkeiten.

Peter Wang (Gründer Anaconda) beantwortet die Frage "Was ist Data Science" so: data science is a literacy, not a job. Ihm zufolge entwickelt sich Data Science mehr und mehr zu einer allgemein notwendigen Fähigkeit, die keinem einzelnen Berufszweig zuzuordnen ist.

Wenn du anfangen möchtest, dich mit Data Science zu beschäftigen, sind Bücher, Videos oder Vorlesungen zu Statistik und Python eine gute Wahl. Für eine umfangende Einführung empfehle ich Onlinekurse, z.B. den genannten von Coursera, siehe Link weiter unten.

Video Title: Statistics - A Full University Course on Data Science Basics
Video Description:
Learn the essentials of statistics in this complete course. This course introduces the various methods used to collect, organize, summarize, interpret and reach conclusions about data. An emphasis is placed on demonstrating that statistics is more than mathematical calculations. By using examples gathered from real life, students learn to use statistical methods as analytical tools to develop generalizations and meaningful conclusions in their field of study. 

🎥 Course by Monika Wahi.

Video Title: Data science for the environment | Dan Hammer | TEDxBerkeley
Video Description:
Since the industrial revolution, as human technology has advanced, the environment has suffered. Dan Hammer is looking to turn this paradigm on its head, as he takes a high-tech approach to preserving the environment by using data science and satellite imagery to monitor and protect forests all around the globe. 
 Dan Hammer received 2017 Pritzker Award for his work to make environmental information more accessible to journalists. He earned his PhD in Environmental Economics from UC Berkeley, where he was a Fellow at the Berkeley Institute for Data Science. Dan works at an environmental and tech nonprofit that he founded alongside two other Berkeley alumni, including the former CEO of The Nature Conservancy and The Moore Foundation. He previously served as a Senior Policy Advisor on data infrastructure in the Obama White House, as well as a Presidential Innovation Fellow at NASA. Dan was the Chief Data Scientist at the World Resources Institute, where he co-founded Global Forest Watch -- an online platform to monitor deforestation from satellite imagery. This talk was given at a TEDx event using the TED conference format but independently organized by a local community. Learn more at https://www.ted.com/tedx
Channel Description:
TEDx is an international community that organizes TED-style events anywhere and everywhere -- celebrating locally-driven ideas and elevating them to a global stage. TEDx events are produced independently of TED conferences, each event curates speakers on their own, but based on TED's format and rules.

Video Title: Entropy (for data science) Clearly Explained!!!
Video Description:
Entropy is a fundamental concept in Data Science because it shows up all over the place - from Decision Trees, to similarity metrics, to state of the art dimension reduction algorithms. It's also surprisingly simple, but often poorly explained. Traditionally the equation is presented with the expectation that you memorize it without thoroughly understanding what it means and where it came from. This video takes a very different approach by showing you, step-by-step, where this simple equation comes from, making it easy to remember (and derive), understand and explain to your friends at parties.

For a complete index of all the StatQuest videos, check out:
https://statquest.org/video-index/

4:34 Equation for surprise

10:45 Entropy is the expected value of surprise
11:41 The entropy equation
13:01 Entropy in action!!!

Channel Description:

This Machine Learning basics video will help you understand what Machine Learning is, what are the types of Machine Learning - supervised, unsupervised & reinforcement learning, how Machine Learning works with simple examples, and will also explain how Machine Learning is being used in various industries. Machine learning is a core sub-area of artificial intelligence; it enables computers to get into self-learning mode without being explicitly programmed. When exposed to new data, these computer programs are enabled to learn, grow, change, and develop by themselves. So, the iterative aspect of machine learning is the ability to adapt to new data independently. This is possible as programs learn from previous computations and use “pattern recognition” to produce reliable results.

The below topics are explained in this Machine Learning basics video:

Video Title: Guia de carreira DATA SCIENCE | #HipstersPontoTube
Video Description:
5º ep. da Temporada! Com o Guia de Carreira Data Science, aprenda o que é CIÊNCIA de DADOS e quais os caminhos possíveis para atuar na profissão de Cientista de Dados. Começando com o Data Science desde o ZERO com a linguagem de programação PYTHON, passando pela ESTATÍSTICA e a Matemática, Análise Exploratória (extração e tratamento de dados), os Notebooks como o Jupyter Notebook e o Google Colab, até mergulhos mais profundos com SQL, MACHINE LEARNING, Aprendizado de Máquina, Modelos, Algoritmos de Classificação e Regressão, Visão Computacional, PyTorch, TensorFlow, NLP (Processamento de Linguagem Natural) e muito mais!

Sabemos que é comum a procura por um ROADMAP para nortear os estudos e carreira, em busca de solucionar questões como “o que é preciso para ser Data Science?” ou mesmo “quanto tempo para aprender Ciência de Dados?”. Por isso preparamos o GUIA de CARREIRA DATA SCIENCE, para você ter caminhos com Cursos, Formações, Artigos e muito mais, além de construir sua profissão em tecnologia.

Venha conferir! 😎

💻 Capítulos:

00:00 - 03:22 - INTRODUÇÃO — Tech Guide: DATA SCIENCE

03:23 - 04:09 - NÍVEL 01: PYTHON, Extração e Tratamento de Dados e os Fundamentos | Tech Guide
04:10 - 07:59 -  1.1) PYTHON para Ciências de Dados: PANDAS, Scikit-Learn e NUMPY

Video Title: Data Science Competitions - Kaggle & DataHack - Explained in 60 Seconds
Video Description:
Data science competitions are an absolute must for data scientists. They offer a thrilling playground to sharpen skills, showcase expertise while solving real-world problems and competing with top talents worldwide 💪 Icing on the cake is the prize money that's at stake.

Here's your starters guide to get started with Data Science Competitions organised on platforms like: Kaggle, DataHack, etc.


✅ In the beginning 🔥

The competition begins with a captivating problem statement, accompanied by train data, test data, and an evaluation metric.


✅ During the competition 🔥

Participants train their machine learning models using the train data and generate predictions on the test data. During the competition, submissions are evaluated using the public test data, which determines the participants' rank on the public leaderboard. However, this ranking is not final.

Throughout the competition, participants can experiment with various approaches and build multiple models in an effort to improve their rank on the public leaderboard. They strategize and refine their techniques to climb higher.

✅ In the end  🔥

When the competition concludes, participants must select a final submission within the specified deadline, following the competition rules. This final submission undergoes evaluation against the private test data, which is not revealed during the competition. Based on this evaluation, the private leaderboard is published.

The private leaderboard reveals the participants' final rank, which represents their overall performance in the competition. It serves as the ultimate measure of success and determines the winners of the competition.

Are you preparing for your data science interview? Whether you're a fresher or an experienced professional, this video will give you the link to the most asked data science interview questions and help you crack your next data science interview with confidence!

In the redirected video which is Data Science Interview Preparation, we highlight crucial data science interview questions and answers that are frequently asked in FAANG and other top-tier companies. These data science interview questions cover Python, machine learning, and real-world problem-solving, ensuring you're well-prepared for any data science interview scenario.

🔥 FAQs – Frequently Asked Data Science Interview Questions

Q1: What are the most common data science interview questions for freshers?
Freshers often face questions like:

Q. What is the difference between supervised and unsupervised learning?
Q. Explain overfitting and how to prevent it.
Q. How does a decision tree work?
Q. What are feature selection techniques in data science?

Q2: What are key data science interview questions for experienced professionals?
Experienced candidates get more complex questions, such as:

Q. How do you handle missing data in a large dataset?
Q. Explain hyperparameter tuning in machine learning.
Q. What are the challenges in deploying machine learning models?
Q. How do you optimize a SQL query for large datasets?

Q3: How can I prepare for a FAANG-level data science interview?
FAANG interviews focus on:

Q. System design and big data processing
Q. Advanced machine learning algorithms
Q. Python-based problem-solving
Q. Case studies on A/B testing, recommendation systems, and time series forecasting

Q4: How important is Python in a data science interview?
Python is essential! Data science interview questions in Python often cover:

Q. Writing efficient Pandas queries
Q. Implementing machine learning models using Scikit-learn
Q. Handling large datasets with NumPy

Video Title: Complete Python Pandas Data Science Tutorial! (Reading CSV/Excel files, Sorting, Filtering, Groupby)
Video Description:
Try out the Datacamp platform - Assess your skills, learn Python, SQL, R and more... and get certified as a data professional!
https://datacamp.pxf.io/c/3588040/1012793/13294

Data & code used in this Tutorial: https://github.com/KeithGalli/pandas
Python Pandas Documentation: http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/

Let me know if you have any questions!

In this video we walk through many of the fundamental concepts to use the Python Pandas Data Science Library. We start off by installing pandas and loading in an example csv. We then look at different ways to read the data. Read a column, rows, specific cell, etc. Also ways to read data based on conditioning. We then move into some more advanced ways to sort & filter data. We look at making conditional changes to our data. We also start doing aggregate stats using the groupby function. We finished the video talking about how you would work with a very large dataset (many gigabytes)

I realized as I upload this video there are some additional things I want to talk about in a later video. The first thing that comes to mind immediately is using the apply() function on a dataframe to alter the data using a custom or lambda function. If you have questions on this or anything else before I get around to making  a part 2, feel free to write me a note in the comments.

Video Title: Was ist Data Science?
Video Description:
In diesem Video zeigen wir: Was Data Science ist. Dabei geben wir eine kurze Definition von Data Science, stellen die notwendigen Fähigkeiten von Datenwissenschaftlern vor und zeigen exemplarisch Anwendungsfälle aus der Praxis.


Zunächst gehen wir kurz auf die Grundlagen von Data Science ein. Danach erklären wir, welche Fähigkeiten ein Data Scientist mitbringen sollte, damit er Unternehme erfolgreich unterstützen kann, Daten zu analysieren. Folgende Fähigkeiten sollte ein Data Scientist haben:


1. Mathematische und stochastische Modelle und Methoden bilden die Grundlage für die Analyse und Interpretation von Daten. Von großer Bedeutung sind insbesondere eine hohe Datenqualität und die sorgfältige Auswahl der Merkmale von Daten-Stichproben. Zum Einsatz kommen insbesondere auch Verfahren des maschinellen Lernens.
2. Im Zeitalter großer Datenmengen („Big Data“) ist Datenwissenschaft ohne fundierte Kenntnisse über Datenverarbeitung und ihre Instrumente kaum vorstellbar. Die Computer-Wissenschaft (Informatik) unterstützt die Big-Data-Analyse durch Algorithmen, die für eine effiziente Bearbeitung der jeweiligen Datentypen geeignet sind. Analyse-Tools selektieren aus strukturierten oder unstrukturierten Datenmengen die benötigten wertvollen Informationen. 
3. Spezifische Branchen-Kenntnisse sind unerlässlich, um Daten und Geschäftsprozesse eines bestimmten Unternehmens einordnen und analysieren sowie sinnvolle Handlungsempfehlungen entwickeln zu können. Betriebswirtschaftliches Wissen ist von grundlegender Bedeutung, wenn Datenanalysen zwecks Geschäftsoptimierung durchgeführt werden sollen.



Zum Schluss zeigen wir Anwendungsfälle und Beispiele von Data Science aus der Praxis. Damit wollen wir das Potential von maschinellem Lernen und Data Science für Unternehmen zeigen. 


Nachdem Sie dieses Video gesehen haben, wissen Sie was Data Science ist, welche Fähigkeiten ein Data Scientist haben muss, um erfolgreich zu ein und wie Sie Data Science in der Praxis für sich nutzen können.


Wenn Ihnen das Video gefallen hat, dann abonnieren Sie unseren Youtube-Kanal für weitere spannende Videos rund um das Thema künstliche Intelligenz und maschinelles Lernen im Marketing.


Den Artikel zu Data Science finden Sie auch auf unserem Blog: 

https://datasolut.com/was-ist-data-science/
Channel Description:

Video Title: Skills Required to Become a Data Analyst in 2025 | Data Analyst Skills | Intellipaat #shorts
Video Description:
In this conversational #shorts, we interview a professional Data Analyst to uncover the Skills Required to Become a Data Analyst in 2025! 🎯 From technical skills like SQL, Excel, and Python to critical thinking and data visualization, learn what it takes to succeed in this fast-growing field. Watch now to get insider tips on becoming a successful Data Analyst!

#DataAnalyst #DataAnalysis #DataSkills #JobSkills #Intellipaat #SQL #Python #Shorts #DataAnalystShorts #TechShorts #ShortsVideo #ShortsFeed #YTShorts #YouTubeShorts #Intellipaat

💡What are the skills needed for a data analyst?
A data analyst needs strong skills in data analysis tools like Excel, SQL, and Python or R. Knowledge of data visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI is essential for presenting insights. They should also have critical thinking abilities to interpret data and problem-solving skills to provide actionable insights from complex datasets.

💡What is required for data analyst job?
For a data analyst job, you'll need proficiency in data tools like Excel, SQL, and Python, along with strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Familiarity with data visualization tools such as Tableau is crucial. Additionally, a good understanding of statistics and business acumen is beneficial.

Video Title: Data Analysis with Python - Full Course for Beginners (Numpy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn)
Video Description:
Learn Data Analysis with Python in this comprehensive tutorial for beginners, with exercises included!
NOTE: Check description for updated Notebook links.

Data Analysis has been around for a long time, but up until a few years ago, it was practiced using closed, expensive and limited tools like Excel or Tableau. Python, SQL and other open libraries have changed Data Analysis forever.

In this tutorial you'll learn the whole process of Data Analysis: reading data from multiple sources (CSVs, SQL, Excel, etc), processing them using NumPy and Pandas, visualize them using Matplotlib and Seaborn and clean and process it to create reports.
Additionally, we've included a thorough Jupyter Notebook tutorial, and a quick Python reference to refresh your programming skills.

💻 Course created by Santiago Basulto from DataWars
🔗 Check out all Data Science courses from DataWars: https://datawars.io/ref=fcc

⚠️ Note: Instead of loading the notebooks on notebooks.ai, you should use Google Colab instead. Here are instructions on loading a notebook directly from GitHub into Google Colab: https://colab.research.google.com/github/googlecolab/colabtools/blob/master/notebooks/colab-github-demo.ipynb#scrollTo=K-NVg7RjyeTk

❤️ Try interactive Python courses we love, right in your browser: https://scrimba.com/freeCodeCamp-Python (Made possible by a grant from our friends at Scrimba)

 ⭐️ Course Contents ⭐️
⌨️ Part 1: Introduction
What is Data Analysis, why Python?, what other options are there? what's the cycle of a Data Analysis project? What's the difference between Data Analysis and Data Science?
🔗 Slides for this section: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1XXhVx2a7z2GrG5qddIyLFk4T_5s5mmdqSptDGBD9hWk/edit?usp=sharing

⌨️ Part 2: Real Life Example of a Python/Pandas Data Analysis project (00:11:11)
A demonstration of a real life data analysis project using Python, Pandas, SQL and Seaborn. Don't worry, we'll dig deeper in the following sections
🔗 Notebooks: https://github.com/rmotr-curriculum/FreeCodeCamp-Pandas-Real-Life-Example

⌨️ Part 3: Jupyter Notebooks Tutorial (00:30:50)
A step by step tutorial to learn how to use Juptyer Notebooks
🔗 Twitter Cheat Sheet: https://twitter.com/rmotr_com/status/1122176794696847361
🔗 Notebooks: https://github.com/rmotr-curriculum/ds-content-interactive-jupyterlab-tutorial

⌨️ Part 4: Intro to NumPy (01:04:58)
Learn why NumPy was such an important library for the data-processing world in Python. Learn about low level details of computations and memory storage, and why tools like Excel will always be limited when processing large volumes of data.
🔗 Notebooks: https://github.com/rmotr-curriculum/freecodecamp-intro-to-numpy

⌨️ Part 5: Intro to Pandas (01:57:08)
Pandas is arguably the most important library for Data Processing in the Python world. Learn how it works and how its main data structure, the Data Frame, compares to other tools like spreadsheets or DFs used for Big Data
🔗 Notebooks: https://github.com/rmotr-curriculum/freecodecamp-intro-to-pandas

⌨️ Part 6: Data Cleaning (02:47:18)
Learn the different types of issues that we'll face with our data: null values, invalid values, statistical outliers, etc, and how to clean them.
🔗 Notebooks: https://github.com/rmotr-curriculum/data-cleaning-rmotr-freecodecamp

⌨️ Part 7: Reading Data from other sources (03:25:15)
🔗 Notebooks: https://github.com/rmotr-curriculum/RDP-Reading-Data-with-Python-and-Pandas

⌨️ Part 8: Python Recap (03:55:19)
If your Python or coding skills are rusty, check out this section for a quick recap of Python main features and control flow structures.
🔗 Notebooks: https://github.com/rmotr-curriculum/ds-content-python-under-10-minutes

--

Read hundreds of articles on programming: https://freecodecamp.org/news

Video Title: Data Science is Not for Freshers 🚫 (Tamil) | data science career opportunities
Video Description:
🔍 From My Experience: I don't recommend starting a career in data science as a fresher. It requires a lot of time to understand concepts like mathematics, algorithms, statistics, and more in the initial stages.

📚 Alternative Path: While it's possible to do data science without deep mathematical knowledge, you'll need to learn many libraries. As a fresher, it's better to start with data analytics or data engineering roles in data-related jobs.

Video Title: Data Science: Die Wissenschaft der Daten erklärt
Video Description:
Hast Du auch schon mal von dem Begriff Data Science gehört und Dich gefragt, was genau Data Science ist? In diesem Video erklärt Leonie, was man unter dem Begriff Data Science versteht, auf welchen Grundlagen es basiert und wo man damit arbeiten kann bzw. wo es zum Einsatz kommen kann. Viel Spaß beim Anschauen! 


Timestamps 
0:10 Was ist Data Science? 
0:20 Grundlagen 
1:27 Wo Arbeiten Data Scientists? 
3:30 Zusammenfassung 
3:58 Outro 


Was ist Data Science? 
Data Science ist ein aufstrebendes Feld, das sich mit der Gewinnung von Erkenntnissen aus großen Datenmengen befasst. Es kombiniert mathematische und statistische Kenntnisse, Programmierfähigkeiten und domain bezogenes Wissen, um Daten zu analysieren und wertvolle Informationen zu extrahieren. Data Science umfasst verschiedene Aspekte der Datenwissenschaft und Datenanalyse. Durch den Einsatz moderner Tools und Techniken können Data Scientists Muster und Zusammenhänge in den Daten erkennen, um fundierte Entscheidungen zu treffen und Geschäftsprozesse zu optimieren. 

Data Science Aufgaben und Beruf 
Als Data Scientist bist Du für die Durchführung umfangreicher Datenanalysen verantwortlich. Du sammelst, bereinigst und transformierst Daten, um Muster und Zusammenhänge zu identifizieren. Data Scientists entwickeln auch Modelle und Algorithmen für maschinelles Lernen, um Vorhersagen und Empfehlungen zu generieren. Sie arbeiten eng mit Fachexperten zusammen, um die Datenanalyse auf spezifische Anwendungsgebiete anzuwenden. Der Beruf Data Science bietet vielfältige Karrieremöglichkeiten, sowohl in Unternehmen als auch in der Forschung. Als Data Scientist hast Du die Möglichkeit in verschiedenen Branchen wie Finanzen, Gesundheitswesen und E-Commerce zu arbeiten.

বর্তমানে অস্ট্রেলিয়ার একটা স্টেট গভর্নমেন্ট এ শিক্ষা বিষয়ক নীতি নির্ধারণের কাজ নিয়ে ব্যস্ত থাকি। আর অবসর সময়ে কিছু এডুকেশনাল কনটেন্ট তৈরী করার চেষ্টা করি। মূল লক্ষ্য - শিক্ষার্থীদের কোর্স, ইউনিভার্সিটি, উচ্চশিক্ষা এবং ক্যারিয়ার নির্বাচনে সঠিক দিক নির্দেশনা দেয়া আমার "ঠেকে শেখা" অভিজ্ঞতা থেকে।
আমার বকবকানি শুনে যদি কোনো উপকার হয় তাহলে সাবস্ক্রাইব করে আমার সাথে থাকতে পারেন। আমি সব ভিডিও গুলো করি ছাত্র ছাত্রীদের রিকোয়েস্ট এর থেকে |

Video Title: Studium Data Science: Besteht Marie ihre schwerste Statistik-Klausur?  | alpha Uni
Video Description:
Marie ist im 2. Semester im Master-Studiengang “Data Science & Statistics” an der Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität (LMU) in München, wo sie die Pflichtvorlesung “Statistical Inference” in Statistik besucht. Für Marie ist diese Vorlesung inhaltlich das schwerste Modul im “Data Science & Statistics” Master-Studium. Auch Programmieren steht hier auf der Tagesordnung! Zusätzlich zur Veranstaltung wird auch eine Übung angeboten, in der es wöchentlich „Homework-Sheets“ als Aufgabe zu lösen gibt. Diese werden im Anschluss korrigiert und die Studis sehen unmittelbar, wie sie mit dem neuen Statistik-Stoff zurechtkommen. Hat Marie tatsächlich alles verstanden, um gut auf die Statistik-Klausur vorbereitet zu sein? 

Bereits während des Bachelor-Studiums an der LMU München stand bei Marie und ihren Kommilitoninnen und Kommiltonen ein Programmier-Praktikum an. Dabei lernten die Studierenden das Programmieren mit diversen Programmiersprachen und wie sich das für eine große Datananalyse nutzen lässt. Das hat sie inzwischen hinter sich, aber im Master wird’s nicht unbedingt leichter. Wie kommt Marie mit ihrem Data Science Studium und ihrem aktuell schwersten Modul zwischen Programmieren, Statistik und Punktewolken-Plot klar? Und ist sie auf die Prüfung wirklich vorbereitet? In der aktuelle Folge Alpha Uni erfahrt ihr’s!    

Mehr zu den Studieninhalten, Zulassungsvoraussetzungen und Karrieremöglichkeiten findet ihr hier: https://ardalpha.de/s/6FQg5Ak

Channel Description:
Hi, I'm Ken! Data Science, machine learning, AI and Sports Analytics are my passions.  When I was first starting out on my data science journey I was extremely lost. There were very few resources for me to learn about this field from. I decided to start making YouTube videos to share my experiences and to help others learn about data science, machine learning, and AI. 

On this channel I produce fun and informative Data Science content. My goal is to make this field more acessible to everyone through commentary, tutorial, and other educational videos. 

I've been working in the data science field doing sports analytics for the last 7 years. I've held data science positions in companies ranging from startups to fortune 100 organizations.  Hopefully my experience will be valuable to you! 

Check out my podcast "Ken's Nearest Neighbors" for some great interviews with the best in the field!

Video Title: Complete Python Pandas Data Science Tutorial! (2025 Updated Edition)
Video Description:
Hey, what's up everyone? Welcome back to another video! I'm super excited for this one. We're doing another complete Python Pandas tutorial walkthrough. Five years have passed since the last iteration, and both the library and my knowledge have evolved. We'll cover all the basics and advanced techniques to analyze and manipulate tabular data with Pandas. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced user looking to level up, there's something here for everyone. Let's dive in!

What We’ll Cover:
- Setting up your environment
- Introduction to DataFrames
- Loading data from CSV, Excel, Parquet, and more
- Accessing and manipulating data
- Filtering, adding, and removing columns
- Handling missing values
- Aggregating data with GroupBy and Pivot Tables
- Advanced functionalities like shift, rank, and rolling functions
- Exploring the new features in Pandas 2.0
- Using AI tools like GitHub Copilot and ChatGPT to enhance your workflow

Links Mentioned
GitHub Repo (code): https://github.com/KeithGalli/complete-pandas-tutorial
Pandas 2.0 Blog Post: https://datapythonista.me/blog/pandas-20-and-the-arrow-revolution-part-i
Datetime percentage format cheat sheet: https://strftime.org/
Kaggle NOC dataset: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/heesoo37/120-years-of-olympic-history-athletes-and-results

Videos Mentioned!
Olympic Data Cleaning Tutorial: https://www.youtube.com/live/oad9tVEsfI0?si=QeIp8AGcGqrYgzBK
Regex Tutorial: https://youtu.be/vsa9GGzMFXQ?si=tH6vaaKJm5o4Ud93
100 Pandas Problems: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i7v2m-ebXB4&t=47s

Practice!

Analyst Builder: https://www.analystbuilder.com/?via=keith

-------------------------
Video Timeline!
0:00 - Video Overview
1:11 - Getting Started with Python Pandas | Google Colab
1:21 - Getting Started with Python Pandas | Local Environment Setup (Cloning code, using virtual environment, VS Code)
3:58 - Intro to Dataframes |  Creating DataFrames, Index/Columns, Basic Functionality
8:25 - Loading in DataFrames from Files (CSV, Excel, Parquet, etc.)
13:42 - Accessing Data | .head() .tail() .sample() 
15:28 - Accessing Data | .loc() .iloc() 
19:20 - Setting DataFrame Values w/ loc() & iloc()
20:20 - Accessing Single Values | .at() .iat()
21:11 - Accessing Data | Grab Columns, Sort Values, Ascending/Descending
23:01 - Iterating over a DataFrame (df) with a For Loop | df.iterrows()
24:12 - Filtering Data | Syntax Options, Numeric Values, Multiple Conditions
27:58 - Filtering Data | String Operations, Regular Expressions (Regex)
33:09 - Filtering Data | Query Functions
34:20 - Adding / Removing Columns | Basics, Conditional Values, Math Operations, Renaming Columns
41:40 - Adding / Removing Columns | String Operations, Datetime (pd.to_datetime) Operations
46:38 - Saving our Updated DataFrame (df.to_csv, df.to_excel, df.to_parquet, etc)
47:14 - Adding / Removing Columns | Using Lambda & Custom Functions w/ .apply()
50:42 - Merging & Concatenating Data | pd.merge(), pd.concat(), types of joins
58:33 - Handling Null Values (NaNs) | .fillna() .interpolate() .dropna() .isna() .notna()
1:04:05 - Aggregating Data | value_counts()
1:05:47 - Aggregating Data | Using Groupby - groupby() .sum() .mean() .agg()
1:08:24 - Aggregating Data | Pivot Tables
1:10:28 - Groupby combined with Datetime Operations
1:14:38 - Advanced Functionality | .shift() .rank() .cumsum() .rolling()
1:22:10 - New Functionality | Pandas 1.0 vs Pandas 2.0 - pyarrow 
1:25:29 - New Functionality | GitHub Copilot & OpenAI ChatGPT
1:32:05 - What Next?? | Continuing your Python Pandas Learning…

Video Title: Fastest Data Science Roadmap 2024 in Telugu🔥
Video Description:
Fastest Data Science Roadmap 2024 in Telugu🔥

Join our Exclusive Beyond Basics Community: https://beyondbasics.dev/

Fastest Data Science Course (Must Check): https://hubs.la/Q02XtFK60

In this video, we break down the fastest path to mastering data science in 2024! This step-by-step roadmap is designed to help you efficiently reach your goals.

Roadmap with estimated timeframes:

1. Understanding Data Science (2 Days)
- Basics of data science, roles, and career paths.
2. Essential Mathematics (1 Week):
- Statistics (probability, distributions) and Linear Algebra basics.
- Calculus for optimization (focus on gradients).
3. Programming Basics (6 Weeks):
- Python (3 Weeks, Refer this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B25zIPZHU8w&t=7401s)
- SQL (3 Weeks, Refer this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4yEIZ9KZ_aQ&t=3855s)
4. Data Wrangling and Preprocessing (3 Weeks):
- Numpy (1 Week, Refer this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LHzBHo-XZnw&t=3150s)
- Pandas (1 Week, Refer this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b30FUjRbvo0&t=2393s)
- Working on real life datasets (1 Week)
5. Exploratory Data Analysis (3 Weeks):
- Matplotlib (1 Week, Refer this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Wyfku0_yEPw&t=2404s)
- Seaborn (1 Week, Refer this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5TrNuWkwf-M&t=2497s)
- Working on real life datasets (1 Week)
6. Machine Learning Fundamentals (4 Weeks, Full Course on our channel soon)
- Supervised Learning: Linear regression, classification techniques.
- Unsupervised Learning: Clustering and dimensionality reduction.
- Practical applications with Scikit-learn.
7. Advanced Topics: Deep Learning, NLP, Big Data, and Cloud (12-16 Weeks, For High Paying Jobs)
- Deep Learning: Basics of neural networks with TensorFlow/Keras; simple CNN and RNN models.
- Natural Language Processing (NLP): Text preprocessing, sentiment analysis, and basic NLP models using NLTK and Transformers.
- Big Data: Intro to Hadoop and Spark for large datasets; working with RDDs and NoSQL databases.
- Cloud Computing: Setting up AWS/GCP, cloud storage, and deploying ML/DL models with SageMaker or AI Platform.
8. Real-World Projects and Portfolio Building (2-3 Weeks)
- Industry ready Projects to showcase your skills.
- Building a portfolio/strong resume to demonstrate your expertise.

Estimated total time - 20 Weeks provided that you work 4-6 hrs/day (Excluding Advanced Topics)

Video Title: Should you take BTech in Data Science and Artificial Intelligence ? | Career Series
Video Description:
Pros and Cons of Pursuing a BTech in Data Science & AI: A Guide for High School Students with Online Course Recommendations
Are you a student considering a BTech in Data Science and AI? In this vlog, we explore the advantages and challenges of pursuing a degree in these fast-growing fields. We'll discuss the importance of foundational mathematics, aptitude, and genuine interest, as well as the career opportunities available to graduates. By understanding the pros and cons, you'll be better equipped to make an informed decision about your academic and career path.

In this vlog, you'll learn:

The key factors to consider before pursuing a BTech in Data Science and AI
The benefits of having a strong foundation in mathematics and the right aptitude for the subjects
The potential consequences of choosing a degree based on hype rather than genuine interest
How short online courses can help you assess your aptitude and passion for Data Science and AI, including recommendations like Coursera's "Introduction to AI" by IBM, edX's "CS50's Introduction to Artificial Intelligence with Python" by Harvard University, and Udacity's "Intro to Machine Learning with PyTorch and TensorFlow" Nanodegree program

Tips for making an informed decision on whether a BTech in Data Science and AI is right for you
Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe for more insights on educational and career choices! #DataScience #ArtificialIntelligence #BTech #HighSchoolStudents #CareerGuidance #OnlineCourses

Welcome to the ultimate guide to becoming a Data Scientist! 🚀 If you've been wondering how to become a data scientist, how to learn data science, or how to become a data analyst, you're in the right place. In this video, we'll explore the data scientist roadmap, providing insights into how to become a data scientist in 2023 and the steps to fast-track your journey into the world of data science jobs.

🔍 Data Science Basics:

Discover what is data science and its significance.
Get started with data science for beginners and explore the fundamental data science roadmap.
💡 Learn the Skills:

Understand the essential skills required for a data scientist.
Dive into the mathematics fundamentals, covering algebra, calculus, and probability.
Learn programming with Python or R, including basic syntax and Jupyter Notebooks.
📊 Data Manipulation and Visualization:

Explore data manipulation and visualization techniques.
Learn where to find datasets and how to clean and preprocess data.
Master data visualization using popular libraries like Matplotlib and Seaborn.
🧠 Machine Learning Fundamentals:

Delve into supervised and unsupervised learning.
Learn evaluation metrics such as Log Loss, Confusion Matrix, and F1 Score.
📈 Advanced Topics:

Explore advanced machine learning concepts, including ensemble methods and neural networks.
Optionally, delve into big data technologies like Hadoop, MapReduce, and Apache Spark.
🌐 Specialization:

Discover specialized areas like computer vision, reinforcement learning, and time series analysis.
Understand the deployment of models in real-world scenarios and build APIs.
🤔 Important Takeaways:

Don't just follow the trend for money; understand the field deeply.
Data Science pays well, but it demands significant effort and dedication.

Video Title: 2025 The The Intersection of Ethics, Data Science, Informatics, and Epidemiology
Video Description:
On ethics, science, and society—how do we make health data work for everyone? In today’s world, health data are everywhere—they help scientists track disease outbreaks, notice health trends, and improve medical care. All these data come with important questions: Who has access to them? How are they used? Is their use fair and safe for everyone? This symposium explores how experts from different fields—ethics, data science, informatics, and epidemiology—work together to make sure health data are used responsibly. We will discuss real-world challenges like protecting people’s privacy, getting consent before using personal data, and ensuring that health decisions are fair for all communities, especially those who have been—and continue to be—underrepresented, underprivileged, or underserved (the "triple Us"). By bringing together different viewpoints, we can understand how to make public health efforts effective, ethical, transparent, and just.

Hosted March 20, 2025
Channel Description: The Georgetown-Howard Universities Center for Clinical and Translational Science (GHUCCTS) is a multi-institutional consortium of medical research institutions forged from a desire to promote clinical research and translational science. The members of the GHUCCTS consortium are: Georgetown University (GU), Howard University (HU), MedStar Health Research Institute (MHRI), Oak Ridge National Laboratory (ORNL), and the Washington Veteran’s Affairs Medical Center (VAMC).

Video Title: Top Data Analysis interview questions for Freshers
Video Description:
Interview Questions for Data Analyst Fresher:-

✅Q1. What experience do you have with data analysis?
Ans: As a fresher, I do not have any professional experience in data analysis. However, I have completed several data analysis projects during my academic studies, where I worked on cleaning and analyzing data to identify trends and insights.

✅Q2. What programming languages do you know, and how do you use them in data analysis?
Ans: I have experience with programming languages like Python, R, and SQL. I use Python and R for statistical analysis, data visualization, and modeling, while SQL is used to extract data from databases.

✅Q3. What statistical methods do you use to analyze data?
Ans :I am familiar with various statistical methods like hypothesis testing, regression analysis, clustering, and time-series analysis, which I use to analyze data.

✅Q4. Describe a time when you identified a data-related problem and how you solved it.
Ans: During one of my data analysis projects, I encountered a missing data problem. I solved it by imputing the missing data using the mean or median of the data. I also checked if there was any bias in the data due to the missing values.

✅Q5. What is your experience with data visualization tools and techniques?
Ans: I have experience with data visualization tools like Power BI. I use them to create interactive dashboards, charts, and graphs to communicate the insights and trends in the data.

✅Q6. What is your experience with SQL and databases, and how do you use them in data analysis?
Ans: I have experience with SQL and databases. I use SQL to extract data from databases and create queries to manipulate and analyze the data.

✅Q7. How do you ensure the accuracy and reliability of your data analysis results?
Ans: To ensure the accuracy and reliability of my data analysis results, I validate the data sources, perform quality checks on the data, use appropriate statistical methods, and document my analysis process.

Aditi Gupta
Analytics Mentor

#powerbi #powerbidesktop #interviewtips #interviewquestions #interviewpreparation

💡What are the skills needed for a data analyst?
A data analyst needs strong skills in data analysis tools like Excel, SQL, and Python or R. Knowledge of data visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI is essential for presenting insights. They should also have critical thinking abilities to interpret data and problem-solving skills to provide actionable insights from complex datasets.

💡What is required for data analyst job?
For a data analyst job, you'll need proficiency in data tools like Excel, SQL, and Python, along with strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Familiarity with data visualization tools such as Tableau is crucial. Additionally, a good understanding of statistics and business acumen is beneficial.

Video Title: Must learn Excel topics for Data Analysts
Video Description:
Excel Skills for Data and Business Analysts

🎯 As a Data or Business Analyst, Excel is an essential tool for driving insights and informing business decisions. 

🎯 To stay ahead, focus on mastering these critical Excel topics:

1. *Data Manipulation*: 
PivotTables, VLOOKUP, INDEX-MATCH, and Power Query.

2. *Data Visualization*: 
Charts, Tables, and Conditional Formatting.

3. *Data Analysis*: 
Regression, Correlation, and Statistical Functions.

4. *Data Management*: 
Data Validation, Data Cleaning, and Data Organization.

5. *Automation*: 
Macros, VBA, and Excel Add-ins.

6. *Advanced Formulas*: 
Array Formulas, Dynamic Ranges, and Named Ranges.

7. *Data Modeling*: 
Data Structures, Data Relationships, and Data Visualization Best Practices.

8. *Power BI Integration*: 
Connecting Excel to Power BI for enhanced analytics.

9. *Advanced Charting*: 
Waterfall Charts, Heat Maps, and Interactive Dashboards.

10. *Best Practices*: 
Efficiency, Accuracy, and Presentation.

🎯 Invest time in mastering these topics to elevate your Excel skills and drive business impact.

For those of you, who are wondering what is “Analytics Vidhya”, “Analytics” can be defined as the science of extracting insights from raw data. 

The spectrum of analytics starts from capturing data and evolves into using insights/trends from this data to make informed decisions. 

“Vidhya” on the other hand is a Sanskrit noun meaning “Knowledge” or “Clarity on a subject”. Knowledge, which has been gained through reading literature or through self-practice / experimentation.

Video Title: Learn 80% of Data Analysis in Excel in Just 12 Minutes
Video Description:
Learn Data Analysis Essentials in Excel in Just 12 minutes!
🚀 Take our Data Analyst Program here: https://www.careerprinciples.com/career-track/the-data-analyst-program

🆓 DOWNLOAD Free Excel Dataset file for this video: https://careerprinciples.myflodesk.com/hnvo5wptlf

In this tutorial using a real-world dataset on the Olympics, we go over the 4 core steps of data analysis in excel. First, we clean up the data. For this, we create a backup of the raw dataset, remove duplicates, and more. Then, we transform the data. This includes replacing certain values, filling in the blanks, and using the TRIM and PROPER functions to clean up. Third, we do the analysis with Pivot Tables and functions, where our manager is asking us a series of questions. Finally, we visualize the data with charts and pivot table slicers.

Video Title: Data Analysis with Python - Full Course for Beginners (Numpy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn)
Video Description:
Learn Data Analysis with Python in this comprehensive tutorial for beginners, with exercises included!
NOTE: Check description for updated Notebook links.

Data Analysis has been around for a long time, but up until a few years ago, it was practiced using closed, expensive and limited tools like Excel or Tableau. Python, SQL and other open libraries have changed Data Analysis forever.

In this tutorial you'll learn the whole process of Data Analysis: reading data from multiple sources (CSVs, SQL, Excel, etc), processing them using NumPy and Pandas, visualize them using Matplotlib and Seaborn and clean and process it to create reports.
Additionally, we've included a thorough Jupyter Notebook tutorial, and a quick Python reference to refresh your programming skills.

Video Title: Data Analyst vs Data Scientist | Difference between Data Analyst and Data Scientist | Must Watch
Video Description:
🔥🔥Difference between Data Analyst and Data Scientist.🔥🔥
---------------------------------
Data Analysts 🔥
----------------------------------
✅Data detectives.
✅Gather, process, and analyze large datasets.
✅Perform statistical analyses.
✅Goal: Uncover trends, correlations, and insights for business decisions.
--------------------------
Data Scientists 🔥
---------------------------
✅Wizards of data.
✅Analyze data.
✅Develop algorithms and predictive models.
✅Goal: Forecast future trends by working with complex datasets.

--------------------------
Key Differences🔥
----------------------------
Data Analysts🔥
---------------------------
✅Analyze existing data.
✅Provide reports.

Data Scientists🔥
----------------------------
✅Forecast future trends.
✅Build predictive models.
✅Work with more complex datasets.

A massive amount of data that cannot be stored, processed, and analyzed using the traditional ways is known as Big Data. What Is Big Data?
Big data refers to the vast volume, variety, and velocity of data that exceeds traditional processing methods. It encompasses structured, unstructured, and semi-structured data from various sources, offering valuable insights for informed decision-making. Big data requires advanced analytics and scalable infrastructure to extract patterns, optimize operations, and gain comprehensive understanding for transformative impact.

#DataAnalyst #DataAnalysis #DataSkills #JobSkills #Intellipaat #SQL #Python #Shorts #DataAnalystShorts #TechShorts #ShortsVideo #ShortsFeed #YTShorts #YouTubeShorts #Intellipaat

💡What are the skills needed for a data analyst?
A data analyst needs strong skills in data analysis tools like Excel, SQL, and Python or R. Knowledge of data visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI is essential for presenting insights. They should also have critical thinking abilities to interpret data and problem-solving skills to provide actionable insights from complex datasets.

💡What is required for data analyst job?
For a data analyst job, you'll need proficiency in data tools like Excel, SQL, and Python, along with strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Familiarity with data visualization tools such as Tableau is crucial. Additionally, a good understanding of statistics and business acumen is beneficial.

Video Title: Learn SQL for Data Analysis in one hour (with sample dataset + 50 queries)
Video Description:
SQL is one of the most important skills to have for data people. In this comprehensive video, learn how to use SQL to perform common data analysis tasks. You will learn:

◈ How to use SELECT statement to answer business questions
◈ Working with WHERE clause
◈ Using AND, OR, NOT and combining them to create complex queries.
◈ Sorting query results using ORDER BY
◈ Combining data from two or more tables using JOINS
◈ Creating reports with GROUP BY
◈ More than 50 example queries, tips and ideas

🚨 PRE-REQUISITES:

You need any SQL console (I am using the FREE MySQL Community Edition and you can download it from https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/installer/ )
You also need the Awesome Chocolates Dataset.
See https://chandoo.org/wp/learn-sql-for-data-analysis/ for the sample files, instructions on data import and other SQL resources for you.

57:12 - Closing remarks & next steps for you

3 Data Analysis Projects to Boost Your Resume 
👋 Hey everyone! I'm thrilled to share some of my proudest achievements in the world of data analysis. Over the past year, I've dived deep into some fascinating projects that showcase my skills and passion for turning data into actionable insights. Here's a sneak peek into three standout projects that have enriched my resume:

1️⃣ Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) for E-commerce Sales
Using Python, Pandas, and various visualization libraries, I analyzed a real e-commerce dataset to uncover trends, segment customers, and evaluate product performance. This project honed my skills in data cleaning, manipulation, and visualization. It's a foundational project that every data analyst should master. Check out my GitHub for all the details!

2️⃣ Movie Recommendation System
Leveraging collaborative filtering techniques, I built a recommendation system with Python and machine learning libraries using the MovieLens dataset. This project not only enhanced my data manipulation abilities but also gave me hands-on experience with machine learning algorithms and model evaluation. It's a perfect example of practical machine learning applications. Explore the code on my GitHub!

3️⃣ Stock Market Analysis and Prediction
I analyzed historical stock market data and developed a basic prediction model using ARIMA. This project involved data acquisition from financial APIs, time series analysis, and forecasting techniques. It's a great demonstration of my ability to handle financial data and predict market trends. Dive into the project on my GitHub!

💡 Did you know? According to a study by the Harvard Business Review, data analysis is one of the most in-demand skills in today's job market, with companies increasingly relying on data-driven decision-making. These projects not only showcase my technical abilities but also my readiness to tackle real-world challenges in the data domain.

Video Title: Data Analyst Salary in India | Skills Required to Become a Data Analyst | Data Analyst Job
Video Description:
Data Analyst Salary (2-3 Years of Experience)


Based on industry trends and national averages, a data analyst with 2-3 years of experience in India can expect a competitive salary ranging from:


- Average: ₹5,50,000 - ₹8,50,000 per year
- High-end: ₹12,00,000 - ₹15,00,000 per year


Factors influencing salary:


- Location (city, state)
- Industry (finance, healthcare, technology)
- Company size and type
- Specific skills (SQL, Python, Tableau, Power BI)
- Certifications (Google Analytics, Microsoft Certified)


City-wise salary ranges:


- Bengaluru: ₹6,50,000 - ₹10,50,000
- Delhi/NCR: ₹6,00,000 - ₹9,50,000
- Mumbai: ₹5,50,000 - ₹9,00,000
- Chennai: ₹5,00,000 - ₹8,00,000
- Hyderabad: ₹5,50,000 - ₹8,50,000


Sources:

- Glassdoor
- Indeed
- LinkedIn
- PayScale
- AmbitionBox
