Video Title: Build a Career in Data Analytics by 2024 | Career Tips | LearnTube Pro
Video Description:
With 3 months and 19 days left for 2023 to end, it is time to start thinking of your career in Data Science! If you want to turn that dream into reality and conquer 2024, here are the practical steps you should follow:

1) Learn and Grow: Start by honing your data analysis skills. Get familiar with programming languages like Python and R. Also, get comfortable with tools for visualizing data.
2) Showcase Your Work: Create a collection of your data analysis projects. This will impress potential employers and clients.
3)  Gain Experience: Do internships or take up freelance projects. This not only adds to your resume but can also lead to full-time roles.
4) Keep Learning: The data field is always changing. Stay updated with the latest tools, trends, and technologies to stay competitive.
5) Soft Skills Matter: Develop strong communication and problem-solving skills. These are invaluable when explaining complex findings to non-technical stakeholders.
6) Specialize: Consider focusing on a niche area of data analysis, like machine learning or business intelligence, to stand out.
7)  Apply Smartly: Apply for jobs that fit you and customize your resume and cover letter for each one. This makes a big difference.
If you aspire to become a high-earning data analyst by 2024, here's the roadmap to follow. The average annual salary for data analysts has been on a consistent rise, spanning from ₹4,00,000 to ₹12,00,000 or even higher, depending on your proficiency and experience.

Video Title: 🔥Data Analyst Vs Data Scientist | Which is better for you ? #Shorts #Simplilearn
Video Description:
In this video on Data Analyst Vs Data Scientist, we dive deep into the world of data to explore the key differences between Data Analysts and Data Scientists. If you're considering a career in data or just curious about the roles, this video is perfect for you! We'll break down the primary responsibilities, skill sets, and tools used by Data Analysts and Data Scientists, helping you understand what sets these two crucial positions apart.

A Data Analyst typically focuses on interpreting existing data to generate actionable insights for business decision-making. They are skilled in data visualization, SQL, and statistical analysis, working closely with various departments to optimize processes and strategies.

On the other hand, a Data Scientist goes a step further by building models to predict future trends and uncover deeper insights. They leverage advanced programming skills, machine learning algorithms, and big data technologies to solve complex problems and drive innovation.

By the end of this video, you'll have a clear understanding of which career path might be the best fit for you based on your interests and skillset. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe for more insightful content on data careers and trends. If you have any questions, drop them in the comments below!

Data Analysts interpret existing data, while Data Scientists predict future trends with advanced models.

✅What skills do Data Analysts need?

Data Analysts need skills in data visualization, SQL, and statistical analysis.

✅What tools do Data Scientists use?

Data Scientists use Python, R, machine learning frameworks, and big data technologies.

Video Title: How can Dax functions solve Data Analysis problems ?
Video Description:
🚀DAX -Data Analysis Expressions, functions are incredibly powerful and can solve a wide range of data analysis problems in Power BI.
Here are some examples:

1️⃣ Calculating Totals and Averages:
Use the SUM and AVERAGE functions to calculate totals and averages of numeric columns.

👉Example: SUM[SalesAmount] to get the total sales amount.

2️⃣ Conditional Calculations:
Use the IF function to create conditional calculations.

👉Example: IF[SalesAmount (greaterthan) 5000, "High", "Low"] to categorize sales as high or low.

3️⃣ Filtering Data:
Use the CALCULATE function to modify the context of a calculation and apply filters.

👉Example: CALCULATE[SUM(SalesAmount), (Region) = "East"] to get the total sales amount for the East region.

4️⃣ Time Intelligence:
Use functions like DATEADD, PARALLELPERIOD, and TOTALYTD to perform time-based calculations.

👉Example: TOTALYTD[SUM[SalesAmount], [Date]] to calculate the year-to-date total sales amount.

5️⃣Creating Relationships:
Use the RELATED function to bring in data from related tables.

👉Example: RELATED[Customer[CustomerName]] to get the customer name from the related Customer table.

Video Title: عايز تبقي محلل بيانات محترف؟ الفيديو ده ليك 📊 | الخلاصة في تحليل البيانات|#DataAnalysis
Video Description:
📊 خريطة تعلم تحليل البيانات: دليل شامل للمبتدئين
تحليل البيانات أصبح واحد من أهم المهارات المطلوبة في سوق العمل اليوم. إذا كنت مهتمًا بتعلم تحليل البيانات، هنا خارطة الطريق التي ستأخذك خطوة بخطوة لتصبح Data Analyst محترفًا. سنغطي الأساسيات التي تحتاجها لبدء رحلتك في هذا المجال الواسع.

اتعلم تحليل البيانات باستخدام بانداس فى الفيديو ده[https://youtu.be/Zubk9ICoJ-0]

00:00 مقدمة
00:24 الرياضيات والاحصاء
00:42 الأكسل
00:54 SQL
01:09 بايثون
01:21 تجهيز وتجميع البيانات
01:39 عرض البيانات والرسوم البيانية
02:01 machine learning 
02:13 Big Data

[https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGbzY-VLUfcpzhB-iyGvju-NMMez_NNP9]


الخطوة الأولى: الرياضيات والإحصاء
تحليل البيانات يعتمد بشكل كبير على الرياضيات والإحصاء. تعلم المفاهيم التالية سيكون بداية قوية لك:

المتوسط (Mean)
الوسيط (Median)
الانحراف المعياري (Standard Deviation)
الاحتمالات (Probability)
اختبار الفرضيات (Hypothesis Testing)
الخطوة الثانية: تعلم برنامج إكسل (Excel)
إكسل من الأدوات الأساسية في تحليل البيانات. يجب أن تتعلم:

الدوال مثل VLOOKUP، SUMIF
الجداول المحورية (Pivot Tables)
الرسوم البيانية (Charts) لعرض البيانات بشكل مرئي
الخطوة الثالثة: تعلم لغة البرمجة بايثون (Python)
بايثون واحدة من أشهر اللغات المستخدمة في تحليل البيانات. يجب أن تبدأ بتعلم:

Pandas: لتحليل ومعالجة البيانات
Numpy: للعمل مع المصفوفات والعمليات الرياضية
Matplotlib و Seaborn: لإنشاء الرسوم البيانية
الخطوة الرابعة: SQL
البيانات غالباً ما تكون مخزنة في قواعد البيانات، وهنا تأتي أهمية SQL. يجب أن تتعلم:

أساسيات استعلامات SQL لجلب البيانات وتنقيحها من قواعد البيانات.
الخطوة الخامسة: جمع وتجهيز البيانات
تحليل البيانات يبدأ من تجميع البيانات وتنظيفها. يجب أن تتعلم تقنيات:

تنظيف البيانات: إزالة القيم المفقودة والأخطاء
تحويل البيانات: تحويل البيانات الخام إلى تنسيق جاهز للتحليل
الخطوة السادسة: عرض البيانات (Data Visualization)
العرض البصري للبيانات يساعدك في فهم الأنماط والاتجاهات. يمكنك استخدام:

Matplotlib و Seaborn لإنشاء المخططات المختلفة
Tableau و Power BI لإنشاء لوحات البيانات التفاعلية
الخطوة السابعة: تعلم الآلة (Machine Learning)
إذا كنت ترغب في الانتقال إلى المستوى المتقدم، يجب أن تبدأ بتعلم مبادئ تعلم الآلة باستخدام مكتبات مثل:

Scikit-learn: لتطبيق النماذج المختلفة مثل الانحدار (Regression) والتصنيف (Classification)
الخطوة الثامنة: البيانات الضخمة (Big Data)
في المشاريع الكبيرة قد تحتاج إلى تعلم كيفية التعامل مع البيانات الضخمة باستخدام:

Hadoop
Spark
نصائح عامة
لا تتوقف عن التعلم! المجال دائم التطور، حاول متابعة كل جديد.
التطبيق العملي مهم جداً: حاول بناء مشاريع صغيرة أثناء التعلم لتطبيق ما تتعلمه.
لو عايز تفاصيل أكتر وجدول زمني لمساعدتك في تعلم كل هذه المهارات بالتدريج؟ 👇
🔗 زور اللينك ده: [https://shorturl.at/4K9wR]

Video Title: 🔥Salary of a Data Scientist | How Much Do Data Scientists Make? | Intellipaat #Shorts #DataScientist
Video Description:
#SalaryOfADataScientist #HowMuchDoDataScientistMake #Shorts #DataScientist #DataScientistSalary #Salary #TechShorts #ShortsFeed #ShortsVideo 

In this #Shorts video, we are in conversation with a Data Scientist and we ask them how much money do data scientist Make? If you're considering a career in data science, or just want to know the potential salary in this high-demand field, this video on salary of a data scientist is just the right thing you need to watch right now. 
  
✅ What factors influence the salary of a Data Scientist?
The salary of a Data Scientist is influenced by several factors, including experience level, location, industry, and the specific skills they bring to the table. Advanced knowledge in areas like machine learning, big data, and specialized tools can lead to higher compensation. Additionally, companies in tech hubs or sectors like finance and healthcare often offer higher salaries due to the critical nature of data-driven decision-making in these industries.

✅ How does the demand for Data Scientists impact their salaries?
The high demand for Data Scientists has a significant impact on their salaries. As more companies rely on data to drive business decisions, the need for skilled professionals who can analyze and interpret complex datasets has surged. This demand, combined with a relatively limited supply of qualified Data Scientists, drives salaries upward, making data science one of the most lucrative careers in the tech industry.

Video Title: 🔥 How Much Does A Business Analyst Make? | Salary Of Business Analyst In India #Shorts #Simplilearn
Video Description:
In this video on How Much Does A Business Analyst Make ?, we’re going to explore what it means to be a Business Analyst and how much you can earn in this role. A Business Analyst plays a crucial role in helping companies make data-driven decisions. They use data and statistics to uncover patterns, predict future trends, and evaluate the potential impacts of different choices on the business. This analysis helps organizations gain valuable insights and significantly improve their decision-making processes.

We'll discuss the essence of business analytics, which involves a detailed examination of a company’s data to identify trends and make informed predictions. By understanding these patterns, businesses can make strategic decisions that enhance their operations and drive growth. This field combines technical skills with business acumen, making it a highly valuable and sought-after profession in today's data-driven world.

Finally, we'll cover the financial aspect of this career. In India, an entry-level Business Analyst typically earns around 10 lakhs per annum (LPA). However, with experience and expertise, the earning potential significantly increases. Many professionals in this field, especially those with over five years of experience, can earn as much as 25 LPA or more. This lucrative earning potential, coupled with the opportunity to make a substantial impact on business decisions, makes a career in business analytics both rewarding and exciting.

Video Title: 🔥 Salary Of Data Analyst  | How Much Does A Data Analyst Make? #Shorts #Simplilearn
Video Description:
In this short on data analyst salary, we'll delve into the factors that influence earnings in this dynamic field. Data analysts are indispensable players in today's data-driven economy, tasked with unraveling insights from vast datasets to drive informed decision-making.

At the heart of a data analyst's skill set lies proficiency in coding languages such as Python, R, and SQL, alongside a solid grasp of mathematics. These technical skills enable them to manipulate and analyze data efficiently, extracting valuable insights. Moreover, adept project management abilities ensure that analyses are structured, milestones are met, and results are delivered in a timely manner.

Remaining updated with industry trends is crucial for data analysts to stay relevant in an ever-evolving landscape. Continuous learning and adaptation to emerging technologies and methodologies empower analysts to leverage cutting-edge tools and techniques in their work. Additionally, effective storytelling skills are essential for translating complex data findings into actionable insights that drive business decisions.

While advanced degrees like a Ph.D. can bolster one's credentials, formal education requirements for data analysts are flexible. Degrees in fields such as computer science, statistics, mathematics, or economics provide a solid foundation for a career in data analysis. However, practical experience and a demonstrated ability to apply analytical skills are often equally valued by employers.

In terms of compensation, salaries for data analysts vary based on factors such as experience, industry, and geographic location. Entry-level positions typically offer modest to moderate salaries, ranging from 6 to 12 lakhs per annum in India. However, with increasing experience and expertise, data analysts can expect their earnings to grow significantly over time.

Channel Description:
My Big Guide चैनल उन लोगों के लिए एक उत्कृष्ट संसाधन है जो हिंदी भाषा में विभिन्न विषयों के बारे में सीखना चाहते हैं। अगर आप हिंदी भाषा में शिक्षा सामग्री ढूंढ रहे हैं, तो My Big Guide YouTube चैनल निश्चित रूप से आपके लिए देखने लायक है। My Big Guide,  Abhimanyu Bhardwaj द्वारा संचालित एक लोकप्रिय YouTube चैनल है। यह चैनल हिंदी भाषा में सबसे लोकप्रिय शिक्षा चैनलों में से एक है।

अभिमन्यु भारद्वाज हिंदी में शिक्षा सामग्री प्रदान करने के लिए जाने जाते हैं। वह अपनी सरल भाषा और स्पष्टीकरण के लिए प्रसिद्ध हैं।  अभिमन्यु भारद्वाज एक प्रसिद्ध यूट्यूबर, ब्लॉगर और शिक्षाविद् हैं। वह हिंदी में विभिन्न विषयों पर वीडियो और लेख बनाते हैं। वह "My Big Guide" नाम से एक लोकप्रिय ब्लॉग भी चलाते हैं।

Video Title: Salary Of Power BI Developer | Power BI Salary In India  #Shorts #simplilearn
Video Description:
In this video on Salary Of Power BI Developer, we will discuss the essentials of Power BI, a powerful tool by Microsoft. In our last conversation, we talked about Business Analysts, and today, we’re focusing on Power BI. This leading Business Intelligence (BI) tool is designed to transform data from various sources into clear, visually engaging, and interactive insights. Whether you're working with spreadsheets, cloud services, or databases, Power BI allows users to create compelling reports and dashboards that facilitate data-driven decision-making.

Power BI stands out for its user-friendly interface and robust functionality. It enables users to connect to various data sources, perform complex data transformations, and visualize data in a way that is easy to understand. With its drag-and-drop features and extensive library of visualizations, Power BI makes it simple for both beginners and advanced users to create insightful reports. Additionally, Power BI integrates seamlessly with other Microsoft products, enhancing its utility for those already using tools like Excel, Azure, and SQL Server.

Mastering Power BI opens up a range of job opportunities in the field of data and analytics. Some of the key roles include BI Analyst, Data Analyst, and BI Consultant. These positions involve analyzing data trends, creating detailed reports, and providing actionable insights to drive business strategies. The demand for Power BI skills is high, as organizations continuously seek to leverage data for competitive advantage.

#PowerBI #MicrosoftExam #DataAnalyst #2024 #Simplilearn 

Q1: What is Power BI and what is it used for?

A1: Power BI is a Business Intelligence (BI) tool by Microsoft designed to transform data from various sources into clear, visually engaging, and interactive insights. It is used for creating compelling reports and dashboards to facilitate data-driven decision-making.

Q2: What job roles can I pursue by mastering Power BI?

A2: By mastering Power BI, you can pursue various job roles such as BI Analyst, Data Analyst, and BI Consultant. These roles involve analyzing data trends, creating detailed reports, and providing actionable insights to drive business strategies.

Q3: What is the expected salary for an entry-level professional with Power BI skills?

A3: Entry-level professionals with Power BI skills can expect to earn between 5 to 6 lakh per annum. As you gain more experience and expertise, the salary can increase significantly, reflecting the high demand for skilled BI professionals.

About the course 

Python has been one of the premier, flexible, and powerful open-source language that is easy to learn, easy to use, and has powerful libraries for data manipulation and analysis. For over a decade, Python has been used in scientific computing and highly quantitative domains such as finance, oil and gas, physics, and signal processing. 

Edureka's Python Certification Training not only focuses on the fundamentals of Python, Statistics and Machine Learning but also helps one gain expertise in applied Data Science at scale using Python. The training is a step by step guide to Python and Data Science with extensive hands-on. The course is packed with several activity problems and assignments and scenarios that help you gain practical experience in addressing predictive modeling problems that would either require Machine Learning using Python. Edureka’s Python course will also cover both basic and advanced concepts of Python like writing Python scripts, sequence and file operations in Python. You will use libraries like pandas, numpy, matplotlib, scikit, and master concepts like Python machine learning, scripts, and sequence.

Why learn Python?

It's continued to be a favorite option for data scientists who use it for building and using Machine learning applications and other scientific computations. Python cuts development time in half with its simple to read syntax and easy compilation feature. Debugging programs is a breeze in Python with its built-in debugger. 

It runs on Windows, Linux/Unix, Mac OS and has been ported to Java and .NET virtual machines. Python is free to use, even for commercial products, because of its OSI-approved open source license.

It has evolved as the most preferred Language for Data Analytics and the increasing search trends on python also indicates that it is the " Next Big Thing " and a must for Professionals in the Data Analytics domain.

Video Title: Here are the Top AI Tools for Research Data Analysis
Video Description:
In this video, I dive deep into the world of AI tools and how they can transform data analysis. AI has become an essential part of data science, helping us extract meaningful insights from complex datasets. I decided to test three popular AI tools to find out which one excels in data analysis: Julius AI, Vizly, and the latest version of ChatGPT.

▼ ▽ Sign up for my FREE newsletter
Join 19,000+ email subscribers receiving the free tools and academic tips directly from me: 
https://academiainsider.com/newsletter/

▼ ▽ MY TOP SELLING COURSE ▼ ▽
▶ Become a Master Academic Writer With AI using my course: https://academy.academiainsider.com/courses/ai-writing-course


I started with a public healthcare dataset, which is perfect for evaluating the capabilities of these AI tools. First, I input the data into Julius AI and was impressed by the range of visualizations it produced, such as the distribution of hospital codes and stay lengths. One feature I particularly liked about Julius AI is its self-correcting mechanism, which ensures the analysis remains accurate.

Next, I tested Vizly. This tool also provided insightful visualizations and added a layer of interactivity with its graphs. I could zoom in and out and interact with the data points, which made the analysis more engaging. However, it had some limitations when dealing with more complex, unstructured data.

Finally, I turned to ChatGPT for data analysis. This tool stood out with its ability to create interactive graphs and its thorough analysis plans. One feature that set it apart was its ability to hold metadata in memory and provide a step-by-step breakdown of its analysis process. ChatGPT was also able to confirm its findings by recalculating efficiency, which added an extra layer of reliability to its results.

AI helps in research by making data analysis more efficient and accurate. Whether you're dealing with structured or unstructured data, these AI tools can provide valuable insights that can drive better decision-making.

What is Python?
Python is a high-level object-oriented programming language developed by Guido van Rossum in 1989 and was first released in 1991. Python is often called a batteries included language due to its comprehensive standard library. A fun fact about Python is that The name Python was actually taken from the popular BBC comedy show of that time, Monty Python's Flying Circus. Python is widely used these days from data analytics, machine learning, and web development. Python allows you to write programs in fewer lines of code than most of programming languages. Python as a programming language is growing rapidly. It's the right time to get trained in Python.

If you’ve ever wondered what Open Interest really means and how it can impact your trades, this video is a must-watch! Whether you're a beginner trying to understand the basics or an experienced trader looking to refine your market reading skills, we’ve got you covered.

In this comprehensive video, we break down how to analyze Open Interest and OI Change data in real-time to identify bullish or bearish trends, support & resistance levels, and market sentiment.

🔍 What is Open Interest (OI)?

🔄 How OI changes during the day and why you must monitor it constantly

🚨 Why is OI important for traders?
Open Interest shows how many contracts are currently active in the market. It helps you understand where the big players are placing their bets, and whether the market is showing signs of strength or weakness.

Whether you're trading Nifty, Bank Nifty, or individual stock options, understanding OI trends can give you a significant edge in the market.

Video Title: What is Exploratory Data Analysis #shorts #eda #dataanalytics #datascience
Channel Description:
For those of you, who are wondering what is “Analytics Vidhya”, “Analytics” can be defined as the science of extracting insights from raw data. 

The spectrum of analytics starts from capturing data and evolves into using insights/trends from this data to make informed decisions. 

“Vidhya” on the other hand is a Sanskrit noun meaning “Knowledge” or “Clarity on a subject”. Knowledge, which has been gained through reading literature or through self-practice / experimentation.

Analytics Vidhya provides a community-based knowledge portal for Analytics and Data Science professionals. The aim of the platform is to become a complete portal serving all knowledge and career needs of Data Science Professionals.

Video Title: هذه هى الكورسات المطلوبة فى مجال ال Data Analysis  من الالف للياء
Video Description:
السلام عليكم .. متابعيني الأعزاء
يشرفنى إشتراك حضراتكم فى القناة وفى حالة وجود أي إستفسارات يشرفنى الرد عليها عبر ترك رساله فى تعليقات هذا الفيديو والرد عليها فوراً، ولتقديم إقترحاتكم للفيدوهات القادمة ولمتابعة كل جديد أدعوكم للتفضل بزيارة الصفحة الرسمية على موقع الفيسبوك Facebook  بأسم Mostafa Attia
والتى يمكن الوصول لها عبر الرابط:
https://www.facebook.com/Mostafa-Attia-946706452161178/


ال Data Analysis لها كورسات كتير أونلاين بمسميات مختلفة وكل كورس فيهم بيخدم نقطة معينة أو مهارة معينة عند ال data analyst
ف دايماً يُفضل لو مش هتاخد منحة مثلاً زي ال ITI أو ALX ، ف الاتجاه الافضل هيكون الكورسات المنفردة أونلاين
مبدأياّ كدا ك Data Analyst مطلوب منك شوية مهارات لازم يكونوا معاكي في البداية ك entry level
1) Soft skills
زي Communication - Questioning - Teamwork - Critical Thinking
دي ال soft skills اللي عادة بتكون ضروري موجودة في ال Data Analyst والحاجات دي لها كورساتها المتخصصة لوحدها لكن في مسار جوجل بتقدمه مكون من 8 كورسات بيركزوا خلالهم إن ال soft skills تتطور فيك بنسبة 70 أو 80% وال 20% الباقيين بيركزوا على جانب ال Technical skills اللي هبدأ أتكلم عنها
بس قبل ما ابدأ ، دا لينك المسار على Coursera
https://www.coursera.org/professional-certificates/google-data-analytics

2) Technical skills 
ودي نقدر نقول شوية Tools وشوية Programming languages
الشركات بتهتم إنهم يكونوا في ال Data Analyst
طب زي ايه؟
- Statistics
لازم على الأقل يكون معايا ال basics ودا ضروري جداً لا غنى عنه، طب اذاكر ايه فيه ممكن يكفيني ك entry level؟ ممكن نتكلم عن ال Descriptive statistics ، وفيما بعد نبدأ نذاكر Inferential statistics و ممكن Probability لو احتاجنا مثلاً نروح لل Machine Learning Engineering
لكن خلينا بشكل مبدأي نروح لل Descriptive statistics 
المصطلحات دي ممكن تبدأي تدوري عليها وتفهمي عنها عشان صعب أشرحها كلها في كومنت
المهم في كورسات كتير جداً بتتكلم عن ال descriptive statistics على يوتيوب ، دا مش معضلة بإذن الله
- MS Excel
مهم تكون بتعرف تستخدمه كويس جداً ويمكن دي أهم tool لازم تكون بتعرف تستخدمها
ودي كورساتها موجوده بكثرة سواء يوتيوب أو غيره
- SQL
دي لغة برمجة بتستخدم لاستخراج الداتا من ال databases ، طب ايه هي ال databases؟ دي مكان لتخزين الداتا بردو بشكل منظم، طب ليه مش بنخزنها في Excel sheet عشان ال database بتخزن داتا أكتر كتير من ال Excel sheet ولأسباب تانية بردو بس دي أهمها
لذلك في شركات عندها كم كبير من الداتا فبتحتاج حد يعرف يتعامل معاها ويستخرجها ودا بيبقى عن طريق ال SQL
ف المهم إني أعرف ال syntax بتاعة ال SQL وبعد كدا أشوف tool ابدأ استخدمها زي على سبيل المثال SQL Server أو SQL Developer
- PowerBI / Tableau
دول اتنين tools من شركات مختلفة وظيفتهم الأساسية هي ازاي ت visualize ال Raw data ال طلعت من ال analysis اللي انت عملتها عشان تبقى مفهمومة لكل الناس

طيب بالنسبة ل SQL و PowerBI و Tableau ألاقي كورساتهم فين
عندك منصات كتير زي datacamp - datascience365 - Udacity 
وكمان اليوتيوب عليها كورسات متفرقة لكن بصراحة كورسات قيمة جداً ، وممكن تكون كورسات مش كاملة بس زي ما بدأت كلامي إن مفيش كورس كامل خصوصاً في ال DA لكن في كورسات متفرقة هتخدم مهارات معينة

حاجة تانية بردو ممكن نلجأ لمنحة ال FWD من وزارة الاتصالات ، بس مش عارف هي لسه فاتحة ولا لأ بصراحة

- Python
دي لغة برمجة ممكن نقول إنها ممكن تقوم بوظيفة ال Excel و ال SQL و PowerBI و Tableau عادي جداً
وفي ناس بتستخدمها ك بديل لحاجة واحدة منهم ، المهم في شركات بنحتاج يكون معاكي Python ودي لغة برمجة هتحتاجي تذاكري ال basics بتاعتها
وال Python كورساته مالية اليوتيوب
بس دايماً أنا بفضل ك بداية كورس مع بشمهندس محمود أحمد (Mahmoud Ahmed) أو في ناس كتير كانت بترشح Codezilla مع بشمهندس إسلام محفوظ
وفي ناس بترشح مذاكرته من الكتب
المهم أنا كان ترشيحي الأفضل هو مذاكرة ال basics مع اللي تستريحله منهم وتدخل بعدها علطول على FWD ، طب ليه ؟ عشان كورسات ال FWD ميزتها إنها بتطبق كل المفاهيم بتاعة ال Data Analysis أو ال Statistics ال هم شرحوها عن طريق بايثون ، ف دي ميزة بتخليك تدرب أكتر على بايثون بالإضافة لفهم أعمق للحاجات اللي اتشرحت
وبعد ما نذاكر ال Python هنشوف tool بتتسخدم بايثون زي Jupyter notebook مثلاً

ف لو جينا ن list الskills اللي أنا قولت عليها
Soft skills .. Descriptive statistics .. Excel .. SQL .. PowerBI / Tableau .. Python (Preferred)

آخر حاجة حابب أتكلم عنها وهي إن للأسف ال titles بتاعة مجالات الداتا كلها داخلة في بعض حالياً ، بمعنى إن للأسف كله بيعمل شغل بعضه ، ف دايماً الأفضل إننا نبص على ال description بتاع الوظيفة هو دا اللي هيحدد المهارات المطلوبة متوفرة فيا ولا لأ

Video Title: StatQuest: Principal Component Analysis (PCA), Step-by-Step
Video Description:
Principal Component Analysis, is one of the most useful data analysis and machine learning methods out there. It can be used to identify patterns in highly complex datasets and it can tell you what variables in your data are the most important. Lastly, it can tell you how accurate your new understanding of the data actually is.

In this video, I go one step at a time through PCA, and the method used to solve it, Singular Value Decomposition. I take it nice and slowly so that the simplicity of the method is revealed and clearly explained.

If you are interested in doing PCA in R see: https://youtu.be/0Jp4gsfOLMs

If you are interested in learning more about how to determine the number of principal components, see: https://youtu.be/oRvgq966yZg

For a complete index of all the StatQuest videos, check out:
https://statquest.org/video-index/

Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/statquest

...buying one of my books, a study guide, a t-shirt or hoodie, or a song from the StatQuest store...
https://statquest.org/statquest-store/

...or just donating to StatQuest!
https://www.paypal.me/statquest

Lastly, if you want to keep up with me as I research and create new StatQuests, follow me on twitter:
https://twitter.com/joshuastarmer

0:00 Awesome song and introduction
0:30 Conceptual motivation for PCA
3:23 PCA worked out for 2-Dimensional data
5:03 Finding PC1
12:08 Singular vector/value, Eigenvector/value and loading scores defined
12:56 Finding PC2
14:14 Drawing the PCA graph
15:03 Calculating percent variation for each PC and scree plot
16:30 PCA worked out for 3-Dimensional data

Channel Description:
Statistics, Machine Learning and Data Science can sometimes seem like very scary topics, but since each technique is really just a combination of small and simple steps, they are actually quite simple. My goal with StatQuest is to break down the major methodologies into easy to understand pieces. That said, I don't dumb down the material. Instead, I build up your understanding so that you are smarter.

Video Title: Thematic Analysis | Explanation and Step by Step Example
Video Description:
Learn the 6 steps of thematic analysis and see an example of how to do thematic analysis using qualitative coding software.

Thematic analysis is a qualitative data analysis method that involves reading through a data set, and identifying patterns in meaning across the data to derive themes.  

Download a FREE Thematic Analysis Guide: https://delvetool.com/blog/thematicanalysis
Start a free trial of Delve qualitative coding tool at https://www.delvetool.com/getstarted
Learn about other Qualitative Research Methodologies: https://delvetool.com/learn


In this video: 
Step by step breakdown of thematic analysis
How to turn data into transcripts
How to derive themes from data
How to craft a narrative from themes
Example of thematic analysis in practice

6 steps of thematic analysis:
1. Familiarize yourself with the data
2. Create your initial codes
3. Collate codes with supporting data
4. Group codes into themes
5. Review and revise themes
6. Write your narrative

Resources from Virginia Braune and Victoria Clarke:
Using thematic analysis in psychology by Virginia Braun & Victoria Clarke: https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1191/1478088706qp063oa
Thematic Analysis: A Practical Guide by Virginia Braun and Victoria Clarke: https://us.sagepub.com/en-us/nam/thematic-analysis/book248481

Welcome to our YouTube channel! In this video, we will take you through an exciting project where we dive deep into Amazon sales data analysis using the powerful combination of Excel and Python. 

In today's data-driven world, analyzing sales data is crucial for businesses to make informed decisions and optimize their strategies. We will guide you step by step through the process, demonstrating how to leverage various Python libraries such as NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, and Seaborn to extract valuable insights from raw data.

Throughout this project, we'll cover the basics, ensuring that viewers of all skill levels can follow along and understand the concepts. Whether you're a beginner looking to learn the fundamentals of data analysis or an experienced professional seeking to expand your knowledge, this video is for you!

Here's a breakdown of what you can expect:

1. Introduction to the project and the importance of analyzing Amazon sales data.
2. Setting up your development environment with Python, Excel, and the necessary libraries.
3. Loading the raw sales data into Pandas DataFrames for efficient manipulation and analysis.
4. Cleaning and preprocessing the data to ensure accuracy and reliability.
5. Performing descriptive statistics using NumPy to gain insights into the dataset.
6. Visualizing sales trends and patterns using Matplotlib and Seaborn.
7. Conducting correlation analysis to identify relationships between different variables.
8. Generating meaningful reports and visualizations to communicate findings effectively.

By the end of this video, you will have a solid foundation in analyzing sales data, using Excel and Python as your go-to tools. The skills you'll gain can be applied to a wide range of real-world scenarios, empowering you to make data-driven decisions and propel your business or career to new heights.

Whether you're an aspiring data analyst, an entrepreneur, or someone who simply wants to harness the power of data, this project is a must-watch. So grab your notepads and join us on this exciting journey of Amazon sales data analysis using Excel and Python!

Video Title: Teach me STATISTICS in half an hour! Seriously.
Video Description:
THE CHALLENGE: "teach me statistics in half an hour with no mathematical formula"

The RESULT: an intuitive overview of distributions, sampling and hypothesis testing that (almost) scrapes in under 30 minutes :) 

Whether you're studying statistics for the first time or are just curious as to what the study of statistics is all about, this video is a great introduction to several core concepts.

Oh, and all the examples I use come from the 2018-19 NBA season.

Steph's 3 point percentage is what is called a 'ratio', which is numeric. It can be argued to be discrete (as for a given number of attempts, there are only so many possible percentages that can be achieved), or continuous (if we allow the number of attempts to change). Heated arguments either way here are semantic, in my opinion :)

See all my videos at http://zstatistics.com/

This is a comprehensive and complete lesson in how to use Power Pivot & DAX Formulas to create reports and visualizations in Excel. It teaches the full process of building a Data Model, Building DAX formulas that you can use for dashboard reporting. This video teaches about the concepts that make Power Pivot work like star schema data modeling, filter context and context transition. If you want the how and whys of Power Pivot & DAX formulas, this is the right video for you.
Topics:
1. (00:00) Intro and overview of Standard PivotTable and Data Model Pivot Table
2. (03:06) 5 Steps in the Data Analysis Process
3. (03:38) Step #1: Get Data using Power Query.
4. (06:12) Show Power Pivot Ribbon Tab.
5. (06:56) Power Query to import text “.CSV” files from a folder, including explanation of Applied Steps and automatic queries created.
6. (11:34) Loading data to the Data Model with Import Data dialog box and using the “Only Create Connection” and the “Add this data to the Data Model”.
7. (12:56) Look at data in Data Model. Preview of Power Pivot for Excel window
8. (13:20) What is a Columnar Data? See how Data is compressed to a small size so that the Data Model can handle Big Data.
9. (15:16) Import Excel Tables to the Data Model using Power Query.
10. (15:29) Decimal Power Query Type is the most consistent Power Query Data Type for numbers with decimals, if you want accurate calculations. If the numbers are whole numbers, use Whole Number Power Query Data Type.
11. (17:01) Step #2: Build Star Schema Data Model.
12. (17:17) Create a Power Pivot Date Table.
13. (19:29) Create One-To-Many Relationships between Fact Table and Dimension Tables.
14. (21:48) Create DAX Calculated Column in Date Table for EOMonth.
15. (24:17) First look at ROW Context to make a calculation in each row in a DAX Calculated Column (or DAX Iterator).
16. (26:05) Create Total Sales Measure with 2 Step Process: 1) DAX Calculated Column for Line Sales, then 2) Measure for Total Sales.
17. (28:56) Second look at ROW Context to calculate line sales in each row of the table.
18. (30:25) SUMX Function, Iterator Function, to create Total Sales Measure. This is 1 Step Method.
19. (32:43) Should you use DAX Calculated Column? Or SUMX Iterator function Measure? What are trade offs?
20. (33:37) Step # 3: Build Reports. Build First Data Model PivotTable to show Year Month Sales Report. Start PivotTable from within Power Pivot for Excel window.
21. (34:48) PivotTable Fields task pane for a Data Model PivotTable. Which table is from Data Model?
22. (36:37) What is Filter Context? Visuals and explanations.
23. (38:44) How Filter Context helps with Big Data.
24. (39:55) Why some columns are not needed in PivotTable list.
25. (39:55) Why Implicit Measures are inefficient and cause problems.
26. (41:50) Hide Fields. Hide From Client Tool. Hide in Report View.
27. (42:57) Sort Month Names in Data Model.
28. (43:41) Step # 4: Visualize. Create Line Chart for Year / Month Sales to see sales trends over time.
29. (45:27) Create Power Pivot Data Model PivotTable from Excel Data tab.
30. (46:39) Create Regions / Year Sales Report.
31. (47:02) Create DAX Formula for YOY % Change. Learn about the DAX functions: CALCULATE, SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR, DIVIDE, HASONEVALUE and IF.
32. (47:54) CALCULATE function. Calculate Total Sales for last year.
33. (53:41) Create DAX Formula for Average Monthly Sales by Product and Year.
34. (54:54) Learn about VALUES function to get a unique list and deliver a table.
35. (55:25) Create AVERAGEX formula.
36. (56:33) Context Transition explanation and diagrams to learn how AVERAGEX and VALUES and the Total Sales Measure calculates average monthly sales with a much simpler formula than in the Excel worksheet.
37. (59:07) Warning about Context Transition. Why aggregate formula yields wrong answer in Iterator function, but Measure yields correct answer.
38. (01:00:15) Hidden CALCULATE function in each Measure. CALCULATE performs Context Transition.
39. (01:01:00) Include Zero Values in average using the IF Function in the second argument of AVERAGEX.
40. (01:02:52) Create Cross Tab Report with Data Model.
41. (01:03:13) Create Frequency Distribution with YOY % Change.
42. (01:04:00) COUNTROWS DAX function. Super Charged COUNTIFS and FREQUENCY.
43. (01:04:50) Using Variables to DAX Formulas. YOY % Change for Number Transactions.
44. (01:07:45) DAX Formatter web site.
45. (01:08:08) Frequency Data Model PivotTable.
46. (01:08:39) Step # 5: Get New Data and Refresh.
47. (01:11:33) Publishing to Power BI Online and making Report from a blank Excel Workbook.
48. (01:13:46) Comparing a Power Pivot Data Model PivotTable to a Standard PivotTable.
49. (01:15:28) Summary.
50. (01:16:04) Next Video

Video Title: Fundamentals of Statistics for Data Analysis | Python Pandas Tutorial for Data Engineering
Video Description:
In this video, we will discuss the foundational concepts of statistics essential for data analysis, demonstrating practical applications using the Pandas library in Python. Perfect for beginners, this tutorial breaks down complex ideas into easy-to-understand steps.

Learn how to transform raw numbers into meaningful insights! This video covers the essential statistics every aspiring data analyst needs to know. We start with the basics: defining statistics for data analysis and why it's crucial. We'll explore different types of data and then dive into measures of central tendency like mean, median, and mode. You'll also learn to measure the spread of data using range, variance, and standard deviation. Understanding data shape with skewness and kurtosis is also covered. Finally, we'll explore correlation, a key method for measuring relationships between variables.

*Topics Covered:*
* Introduction to Statistics and Data Analysis
* Types of Data in Statistics
* Measures of Central Tendency: Mean, Median, and Mode
* Measures of Spread: Range, Variance, and Standard Deviation
* Understanding Data Shape: Skewness and Kurtosis
* Measuring Relationships: Correlation
* Hands-on Pandas Examples with Real-World Data

Using Python and Pandas, we'll apply these concepts to a real-world example: analyzing car sales data for a dealership. Discover how to calculate average sales price, understand price variation, and assess sales rep performance - all using the power of statistics. Whether you're aiming to build machine learning models or simply improve your data analysis skills, mastering these basic statistical concepts is the first step!

Video Title: jamovi for Data Analysis - Full Tutorial
Video Description:
Learn jamovi in this full tutorial course. jamovi is a free, open-source application that makes data analysis easy and intuitive. jamovi menus and commands are designed to simplify the transition from programs like SPSS but, under the hood, jamovi is based on the powerful statistical programming language R. jamovi has a clean, human-friendly design that facilitates insight into your data and makes it easy to share your work with others. In this introductory course, you’ll learn how you can use jamovi to refine, analyze, and visualize your data to get critical insights.

Video Title: ANOVA (Analysis of variance) simply explained
Video Description:
The ANOVA (Analysis of Variance) checks whether there are statistically significant differences between more than two groups. For this purpose, the mean values and variances of the respective groups are compared with one another. In contrast to the t-test, which compares two groups, the analysis of variance compares more than two groups. This Video is about the One-way ANOVA without repeated measurements also called  one factorial Analysis of Variance without repeated measurements

Video Title: DEEP Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) | explore your data and start to test hypotheses
Video Description:
In this video, I'll provide the simplest and the most effective ways to explore data in R, which will significantly speed up your work. Moreover, we'll go one step beyond EDA by starting to test our hypotheses with simple statistical tests... that's what I call "deep" here.

If you only want the code (or want to support me), consider join the channel (join button below any of the videos), because I provide the code upon members requests.

You of coarse don't need to see the whole thing:

Timetable:

00:50 - automated reports as a separate video (https://youtu.be/sKrWYE63Vk4)
02:44 - exploring categorical variables
05:00 - descriptive statistics with some basic tests, like Fishers and Chi-Square, Mann-Whitney and Kruskal-Wallis tests
09:15 - explore distribution with skewness and kurtosis tests
13:03 - explore normality with Quantile-Quantile plots and Shapiro-Wilk normality test
17:20 - compare groups with box-plots and non-parametric tests, like Mann-Whitney and Kruskal-Wallis
19:12 - explore and visualize correlations and get correlation coefficients, confidence intervals and p-values
24:03 - explore linearity of data with non-linear models and ggplot2 package
24:30 - explore and impute NAs as a separate video (https://youtu.be/Akb401i32Oc) and outliers (part of this video)

Here is the code and article about or instead of this video: https://yuzar-blog.netlify.app/posts/2021-01-09-exploratory-data-analysis-and-beyond-in-r-in-progress/

Video Title: Data Analysis using ChatGPT Tutorial: Summarize, Visualize, & Analyze Data with AI!
Video Description:
In this week's video of our Generative AI for IT Professionals series, we explore ChatGPT's powerful file upload and data analysis capabilities. We'll upload an earthquake dataset and use ChatGPT to summarize the data, extract insights, create visualizations, and even generate Python code for further exploration!

*Topics Covered:*
*Can ChatGPT analyze uploaded files? (Introduction to ChatGPT File Upload)*
* Learn how to upload data files (CSV, etc.) into ChatGPT for analysis.

*How do I get a quick overview of my data with ChatGPT? (Data Summarization)*
* Discover how to use ChatGPT to summarize the columns in your dataset and get a sense of the data's structure.

*How do I check for missing values in my data with ChatGPT?*
* We will tell you how to look for missing values.

*Can ChatGPT provide statistical insights from my data?*
* See how to get basic statistics (mean, standard deviation, min, max) for specific columns in your data.

*How do I visualize data directly within ChatGPT? (Data Visualization)*
* Learn how to create histograms, line charts, and even geomaps to visualize your data and identify patterns.

*What kind of charts can ChatGPT generate from my data?*
* We are going to create different types of charts.

*Can ChatGPT Identify patterns? (Pattern and Outlier Detection)*
* Discover how to use ChatGPT to find top values, frequent areas, and outliers in your dataset.

*Does ChatGpt give outputs as a Geo Map?*
* We are going to see if ChatGPT can create and give outputs as a Geo Map.

*How can I generate Python code for Data Analysis with ChatGPT?*
* Learn how to use ChatGPT to generate Python code (using libraries like Pandas and Matplotlib) for more advanced data analysis and visualization.

*What are the different types of Data analysis you can do with ChatGPT?*
* We are going to see different types of data analysis that can be done.

Video Title: Building an Excel Dashboard Using ChatGPT | Data Analysis Project | MS Excel
Video Description:
This video walks you through building a sales analysis dashboard in Excel — first without using ChatGPT, and then with ChatGPT to speed things up. See the difference in approach, effort, and results as we explore both methods step-by-step.

Dataset link - https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ertugrulesol/online-retail-data (Source: Kaggle)

Prompt 1: I want to build an excel dashboard. I have provided you with  the sample data. Carefully analyze this data and suggest what information we should display on the dashboard and how? I want to display some key numbers as well as different graphs that makes it easier for the audience to quickly visualize key metrics and trends. 

_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ 
Prompts for Building Excel Dashboard using ChatGPT 

Prompt 2: ( Insert sample json data format)

This is the structure of my sales data in JSON format. Understand the structure and suggest five key data visualization metrics that would be the best fit to create an interactive sales dashboard. Also explain why we should use each one? 

Include metrics like - revenue by product names, revenue by gender, order count by payment method, sales over time, revenue by category. 

Prompt 3 - Now, I want you to create an interactive sales performance dashboard with the above key visualizations using HTML and JavaScript. Use the latest version of Plotly.js CDN and include an upload feature so that we can upload the JSON file. It should generate the dashboard based on the uploaded data. Note: I need to upload the sales data from my local computer, and it should create the dashboard based on that data.  

Prompt 4 - Provide this as an HTML downloadable file?

Video Title: #18 Exploratory data analysis | Python for Data Science
Video Description:
Welcome to 'Python for Data Science' course !

This video focuses on uncovering patterns and relationships within your data. The lecture introduces frequency tables for understanding the distribution of categorical variables, like fuel type in the car dataset (). You'll learn how to handle missing values when creating these tables. 
It then covers two-way tables for exploring relationships between two categorical variables, for example, fuel type and gearbox type. You'll see how to calculate joint, marginal, and conditional probabilities from these tables to make inferences about variable relationships. 
Finally, the video introduces correlation as a measure of association between two numerical variables, using the car dataset to demonstrate its calculation and interpretation. It emphasizes that understanding these exploratory data analysis techniques is crucial for generating hypotheses and deriving meaningful insights from your data.

Video Title: Hyperspectral Data Analysis with Spectronon: Spectral Angle Mapper & Logistic Regression Classifiers
Video Description:
In this tutorial, we demonstrate how to perform preliminary hyperspectral data analysis using our Spectronon™ hyperspectral software. You'll learn how to apply two powerful hyperspectral classification algorithms — Spectral Angle Mapper (SAM) and Logistic Regression — to classify two different types of red candy.

What You'll Learn:
• How to use Spectral Angle Mapper to classify hyperspectral data using reference spectra
• How to use Logistic Regression to perform pixel-level classification with probabilistic output
• How to interpret colormaps and visualize your classification results

In this example, we classify two types of red candies (Candy A and Candy B) to determine whether any of Candy A appears in a mixed cluster. We use both SAM and Logistic Regression algorithms to show how you can begin to evaluate hyperspectral data you have collected.

Spectronon is our advanced hyperspectral imaging software. It supports a range of machine learning and analysis algorithms, works with user-written plugins, and has an intuitive user interface designed for both researchers and industry professionals. Best of all, it is free for anyone to use and it works with all common hyperspectral datacubes.

Download Spectronon and sample datacubes (including the datacube used in this video) to begin evaluating hyperspectral data: downloads.resonon.com

Learn more about Spectronon, the Spectral Angle Mapper and Logistic Regression algorithms in the Spectronon User Manual: https://docs.resonon.com/spectronon/SpectrononUserManual/SpectrononUserManual.pdf

Keywords: hyperspectral software, Spectronon, spectral angle mapper, hyperspectral logistic regression, hyperspectral data analysis, hyperspectral algorithms

Video Title: Pandas & Python for Data Analysis by Example – Full Course for Beginners
Video Description:
Learn how to use Pandas and Python for Data Analysis, to Data Cleaning and Data Wrangling. You will learn by creating real life projects interactively to help you take the next step in your Data Science Career.

Learn more about the projects at https://www.datawars.io/freecodecamp

⚠️ Important! We encourage you to try to resolve the projects by yourself first! And watch the solution afterwards ⚠️ 

💻 Course created by Santiago Basulto from DataWars.
🔗 Find more interactive Data Science projects solve at: https://www.datawars.io

❤️ Try interactive Python courses we love, right in your browser: https://scrimba.com/freeCodeCamp-Python (Made possible by a grant from our friends at Scrimba)

⭐️ Projects Covered ⭐️
⌨️ (0:00:00) Introduction

⌨️ (0:02:22) DataFrames practice: working with English Words [🟢 Easy]
This project focuses on the basics of pandas DataFrames, including understanding its structures and modifying them. The data we're using is a big dictionary of english words. 
🔗 Solve the project by yourself: https://www.datawars.io/fcc-english-words

⌨️ (0:33:26) Filtering and sorting with Pokemon data [🟢 Easy]
This project focuses on the main tasks of Data Analysis: filtering and sorting and question/answering. The dataset includes information of pokemons from all generations (to make it more fun!)
🔗 Solve the project by yourself: https://www.datawars.io/fcc-filtering-pokemon

⌨️ (1:24:30) The Birthday Paradox in the NBA [🟡 Intermediate]
The Birthday Paradox answers the question: how many people do you need in the same room in order to have a probability of at least 50% that two people share a birthday. The answer is astonishing! You'll use your findings to find which teams in the NBA share player's birthdays.
🔗 Solve the project by yourself: https://www.datawars.io/fcc-birthday-nba

⌨️ (1:55:28) Matching Strings by Similarity using Levenshtein distance [🟡 Intermediate]
One of the most challenging tasks of Data Cleaning is dealing with Strings. This project is all about string handling and advanced techniques, as using the Combinatorics and the Levenshtein distance to find irregularities in company names.
🔗 Solve the project by yourself: https://www.datawars.io/fcc-string-similarity

⌨️ (2:24:15) Data Cleaning with Google Playstore dataset [🟡 Intermediate]
An all-encompassing project that covers all the aspects of Data Cleaning, including: finding and fixing null values, duplicate values, outliers and more. The data was scraped from the Google Playstore which means that is full of irregularities. The project finishes with some Data Analysis tasks!
🔗 Solve the project by yourself: https://www.datawars.io/fcc-data-cleaning-playstore

⌨️ (3:18:34) Premier League Match Analysis [🔴 Advanced]
This project increases the complexity of your Data Analysis skills, as it combines Data Cleaning, with some analysis based on grouping operations. The dataset comes from the Premier League, the top-division Football/Soccer league in England.
🔗 Solve the project by yourself: https://www.datawars.io/fcc-premier-league

⌨️ (3:53:46) NBA 2017 season analysis: joining and groupby practice [🔴 Advanced]
This project puts your Data Wrangling skills to a test, by asking you to merge different dataframes, clean them, and finish doing some analysis and question/answering. The dataset contains the full information of 2017 NBA statistics.
🔗 Solve the project by yourself: https://www.datawars.io/fcc-nba-analysis

Video Title: SQL + Python: Master Data Analysis and Create PDF Reports
Video Description:
👉 Explore All My Excel Solutions: https://pythonandvba.com/solutions

𝗗𝗘𝗦𝗖𝗥𝗜𝗣𝗧𝗜𝗢𝗡
▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀
In this tutorial, I'll show you how to use Python and SQL to transform your data into stunning PDF reports. Whether you're an analyst, a business owner, or just looking to create professional-looking reports for your own use, this tutorial will guide you step-by-step through the process.

First, I'll show you how to set up a SQLite database and load sample data into it using Python. Next, I'll demonstrate how to use SQL queries to extract the data you need from the database. Then, I'll use Pandas to manipulate and transform the data, and show you how to create interactive charts with Plotly Express.

Once we have our data prepped and ready, I'll use the FPDF library to generate a beautiful PDF report.

Whether you're a beginner or an experienced Python user, this tutorial will give you the skills you need to create stunning PDF reports with ease. Follow along, and transform your data into stunning reports that will impress your audience!

🌍 𝗟𝗜𝗡𝗞𝗦:
▶ Source Code: https://github.com/Sven-Bo/PDF-Report-Generator-Using-Python-and-SQL
▶ SQLite Viewer Web App: https://sqliteviewer.app/
